1
00:02:30,687 --> 00:02:32,396
Are you sleeping, Sohrab?

2
00:02:34,187 --> 00:02:36,062
Go in and lie down.

3
00:02:36,062 --> 00:02:37,771
We have to leave
very early tomorrow.

4
00:02:45,729 --> 00:02:47,271
Are you mad at me?

5
00:02:51,687 --> 00:02:52,646
Sohrab?

6
00:02:56,271 --> 00:02:57,771
Hope you know I didn't mean it.

7
00:02:58,271 --> 00:02:59,729
You know that.

8
00:03:00,437 --> 00:03:03,437
Don't know what happened.
I just lost it there for a bit.

9
00:03:04,187 --> 00:03:06,479
I'm really fond of you.
You know that, right?

10
00:03:10,479 --> 00:03:11,479
Sohrab?

11
00:03:31,021 --> 00:03:32,812
Sandeep, wake up.

12
00:04:34,771 --> 00:04:36,562
- Jayanti?
- What's wrong?

13
00:04:37,146 --> 00:04:38,146
What's going on?

14
00:04:39,229 --> 00:04:40,229
Jayanti!

15
00:04:41,187 --> 00:04:42,271
- What's wrong?

16
00:04:44,062 --> 00:04:45,062
Oh my God!

17
00:04:45,187 --> 00:04:48,562
- Maddy, he's been...
- Guys! Let me sleep...

18
00:04:50,062 --> 00:04:51,396
What's going on?

19
00:04:51,521 --> 00:04:52,479
Call the police.

20
00:04:52,521 --> 00:04:56,354
Kumar, I think he's dead.

21
00:04:56,396 --> 00:04:58,562
- What do you mean?
- I think he's dead.

22
00:04:59,479 --> 00:05:00,479
Oh, no!

23
00:05:02,396 --> 00:05:03,396
Oh, no!

24
00:05:14,062 --> 00:05:18,312
Nena, come on.
Let's get out of here.

25
00:05:18,729 --> 00:05:19,646
We can't leave...

26
00:05:19,687 --> 00:05:21,479
What's wrong with you?
You can't leave now.

27
00:05:21,562 --> 00:05:22,604
Says who?

28
00:05:22,687 --> 00:05:23,979
Kumar, where are we going?

29
00:05:24,021 --> 00:05:26,979
- Nena, let's go.
- We can't leave.

30
00:05:27,146 --> 00:05:28,687
- Kumar.
- You don't get it.

31
00:05:28,771 --> 00:05:30,354
All of you'll be fine.
I'll be in trouble.

32
00:05:30,396 --> 00:05:31,396
Kumar!

33
00:05:33,104 --> 00:05:34,729
You can't leave this house.

34
00:05:45,979 --> 00:05:46,979
Isha.

35
00:05:47,229 --> 00:05:48,271
Isha.

36
00:05:49,104 --> 00:05:50,104
Isha...

37
00:06:00,062 --> 00:06:02,354
Why is everyone up?

38
00:06:03,021 --> 00:06:04,229
How come you are awake?

39
00:06:04,271 --> 00:06:07,354
I don't sleep before two.
Finishing up the chores.

40
00:06:17,687 --> 00:06:18,687
'Saheb' ...

41
00:06:20,437 --> 00:06:21,771
'Saheb' is dead!

42
00:06:23,771 --> 00:06:25,021
Did anybody come
from outside?

43
00:06:25,937 --> 00:06:27,604
- Satya?
- No, ma'am.

44
00:06:27,646 --> 00:06:29,437
I locked the gate at 11:30.

45
00:06:29,937 --> 00:06:31,271
- Sure?
- Sure, ma'am.

46
00:06:31,354 --> 00:06:33,271
Not a soul can come in after that.

47
00:06:38,437 --> 00:06:39,562
Tea, anyone?

48
00:06:40,396 --> 00:06:41,354
Ma'am.

49
00:06:41,771 --> 00:06:42,854
Wake her up.

50
00:06:43,562 --> 00:06:45,562
She takes very strong medication.

51
00:06:46,062 --> 00:06:48,396
We can't let her sleep through it.
Move aside.

52
00:06:49,896 --> 00:06:50,896
Isha.

53
00:06:52,812 --> 00:06:53,812
Isha.

54
00:06:55,437 --> 00:06:58,062
Wake up, Isha, please...

55
00:06:59,896 --> 00:07:00,896
Isha.

56
00:07:02,062 --> 00:07:03,062
What happened?

57
00:07:03,271 --> 00:07:04,146
What time is it?

58
00:07:04,312 --> 00:07:06,312
Please wake up.
Something has happened.

59
00:07:06,604 --> 00:07:07,604
It's Sohrab.

60
00:07:08,687 --> 00:07:10,562
What has Sohrab done now?

61
00:07:11,479 --> 00:07:12,479
Calm down.

62
00:07:12,646 --> 00:07:13,562
What did he do?

63
00:07:13,646 --> 00:07:14,896
- Sohrab!
- Please, Isha.

64
00:07:23,771 --> 00:07:25,021
Be careful.

65
00:07:25,771 --> 00:07:28,812
I've been driving carefully
for the last 30 years, Daddy-o.

66
00:07:29,771 --> 00:07:31,437
Not a single scratch on the car.

67
00:07:31,687 --> 00:07:33,771
You don't have to be rude.

68
00:07:33,937 --> 00:07:35,937
You have your seat belt on, right?

69
00:07:36,437 --> 00:07:38,021
Sit back and listen to music.

70
00:07:39,896 --> 00:07:41,396
- Sohrab!
- What?

71
00:07:41,479 --> 00:07:42,896
Drive a little slower.

72
00:07:43,354 --> 00:07:45,146
The roads are pretty bad as it is.

73
00:07:51,771 --> 00:07:53,062
What are you doing?

74
00:07:59,437 --> 00:08:00,437
Is this better?

75
00:08:04,229 --> 00:08:06,771
Stereophonic chorus, you lot!

76
00:08:07,396 --> 00:08:09,979
From one side, be careful.
From the other, go slow.

77
00:08:10,646 --> 00:08:13,479
Should have gone in Sandeep's car
if you wanted to go slow.

78
00:08:14,562 --> 00:08:15,687
Is this better, Daddy-o?

79
00:08:15,812 --> 00:08:17,771
- Sohrab.
- Careful!

80
00:08:20,562 --> 00:08:21,812
You guys are too much.

81
00:08:21,937 --> 00:08:23,271
- Amazing!
- Thank you.

82
00:08:24,562 --> 00:08:25,604
Are you okay, Tiger?

83
00:08:29,479 --> 00:08:30,437
Oh my God!

84
00:08:30,562 --> 00:08:31,562
- Look at that!
- Babe!

85
00:08:32,312 --> 00:08:33,771
- Did you see that?
- What?

86
00:08:33,937 --> 00:08:35,521
Did you see that cottage?

87
00:08:35,896 --> 00:08:38,187
I'm trying to drive.
I can't see anything.

88
00:08:38,687 --> 00:08:39,853
Sorry. I forgot.

89
00:08:40,437 --> 00:08:42,603
I forgot we can't multitask.

90
00:08:42,896 --> 00:08:44,687
That's the truth about my husband.

91
00:08:44,812 --> 00:08:46,187
Why are men like this, Doc?

92
00:08:46,271 --> 00:08:47,854
- Like what?
- Like this.

93
00:08:48,187 --> 00:08:50,812
Can't do more than one thing
at a time.

94
00:08:51,062 --> 00:08:52,979
They miss out on
all that is beautiful.

95
00:08:53,229 --> 00:08:54,521
Always following their nose...

96
00:08:54,604 --> 00:08:55,937
Yeah, men can be like that.

97
00:08:56,062 --> 00:08:57,771
- Unbelievable!
- But you married a good one.

98
00:08:58,812 --> 00:09:00,812
- Hey!
- This is a good one?

99
00:09:00,979 --> 00:09:02,479
- Are you the good one?
- Thanks, Chandra.

100
00:09:02,521 --> 00:09:03,646
He's one of the best.

101
00:09:04,437 --> 00:09:06,312
Your cheque is in the mail.
Thanks!

102
00:09:14,062 --> 00:09:15,521
This is the best chance.

103
00:09:15,937 --> 00:09:17,187
I'm going to talk to her.

104
00:09:18,312 --> 00:09:20,771
- You'd better talk to Raman.
- Will see.

105
00:09:22,562 --> 00:09:24,062
Why are you nodding your head?

106
00:09:24,271 --> 00:09:26,062
Spent your entire life nodding.

107
00:09:27,271 --> 00:09:28,812
They treat you like a peon.

108
00:09:29,187 --> 00:09:31,437
I said, I'd talk to him.

109
00:09:31,771 --> 00:09:34,812
You do all the hard work
and they skim the cream.

110
00:09:36,312 --> 00:09:38,437
No cream, no cholesterol.

111
00:09:39,812 --> 00:09:42,437
The cream is for them.

112
00:09:43,521 --> 00:09:46,312
We were ordained
dry bread.

113
00:09:46,646 --> 00:09:48,312
That's what we get.

114
00:09:49,812 --> 00:09:50,896
Seat belt.

115
00:09:51,687 --> 00:09:52,604
Seat belt!

116
00:10:02,562 --> 00:10:05,396
- Hey, Handa!

117
00:10:05,604 --> 00:10:07,229
- Hi!
- Handa.

118
00:10:09,187 --> 00:10:11,687
Happy anniversary!
You're done for!

119
00:10:11,896 --> 00:10:13,604
- How was the drive?
- It was good.

120
00:10:30,854 --> 00:10:32,729
Oh wow!
Look at this!

121
00:10:32,896 --> 00:10:35,729
- Heavenly!
- Look at these flowers.

122
00:10:38,812 --> 00:10:42,312
- What flower is that?
- It's called angel's trumpet.

123
00:10:42,896 --> 00:10:44,854
- How do you know?
- I know a lot about flowers.

124
00:10:44,937 --> 00:10:46,687
This is better than the pictures.

125
00:10:47,146 --> 00:10:48,812
- I know.
- It is so nice.

126
00:10:50,146 --> 00:10:51,729
Chandra, have you met everyone?

127
00:10:52,271 --> 00:10:55,646
Everybody, wait.
That's Chandra.

128
00:10:56,229 --> 00:10:57,729
- And this is everybody.
- Hi.

129
00:10:58,021 --> 00:11:00,021
Did they tell you
the check-out time?

130
00:11:00,271 --> 00:11:02,646
They say
this was built in the 1920s.

131
00:11:02,854 --> 00:11:03,896
Really?

132
00:11:04,062 --> 00:11:05,187
Hundred years, huh?

133
00:11:05,521 --> 00:11:06,854
Looks it.

134
00:11:07,021 --> 00:11:09,521
- In a good way.
- What a find! Well done.

135
00:11:10,021 --> 00:11:13,146
Sandeep get the bags.

136
00:11:13,437 --> 00:11:14,937
- So?
- This is a find!

137
00:11:15,146 --> 00:11:16,812
- What's your name?
- Satya.

138
00:11:16,896 --> 00:11:18,937
- Is it possible to get some tea?
- With ginger?

139
00:11:19,062 --> 00:11:21,687
- How many rooms?
- Total six, ma'am.

140
00:11:21,896 --> 00:11:22,729
Four in the front,
two at the back.

141
00:11:22,812 --> 00:11:25,187
- All clean?
- With fresh sheets.

142
00:11:25,312 --> 00:11:27,021
Sandeep, give me a cigarette.

143
00:11:28,354 --> 00:11:29,771
- What are you looking for?
- Our room.

144
00:11:29,812 --> 00:11:33,562
Come here. I'll show you your room.

145
00:11:33,729 --> 00:11:35,646
Right here.

146
00:11:35,979 --> 00:11:38,604
Baba, take this room.

147
00:11:38,729 --> 00:11:41,396
Vijaya, settle him
in this room please.

148
00:11:41,437 --> 00:11:42,437
Sandeep!

149
00:11:42,937 --> 00:11:43,937
Sandeep!

150
00:11:45,312 --> 00:11:46,229
Ashtray?

151
00:11:46,312 --> 00:11:47,312
Where's your bag?

152
00:12:00,562 --> 00:12:02,104
Open the window.

153
00:12:03,896 --> 00:12:04,937
Have you gone deaf?

154
00:12:05,062 --> 00:12:07,687
Can't you hear
I am asking you to do something?

155
00:12:11,437 --> 00:12:13,521
Can't leave you alone at home.

156
00:12:13,646 --> 00:12:15,187
Not suitable for polite company.

157
00:12:15,271 --> 00:12:17,062
What the hell
should we do with you?

158
00:12:18,271 --> 00:12:20,771
Must be the punishment for our sins.

159
00:12:20,896 --> 00:12:22,771
Got two demons for sons.

160
00:12:23,437 --> 00:12:25,562
Move away from the window.

161
00:12:25,687 --> 00:12:27,687
Ask Isha to cut some fruits.

162
00:12:28,604 --> 00:12:29,562
Go on.

163
00:12:32,146 --> 00:12:33,687
I'm going to talk to her tonight.

164
00:12:34,396 --> 00:12:36,146
I have a feeling
she'll say yes.

165
00:12:36,312 --> 00:12:39,271
Don't know how you do this.
I'd be petrified.

166
00:12:40,396 --> 00:12:41,604
Oh my God!

167
00:12:42,604 --> 00:12:43,937
Raman, look at this.

168
00:12:44,062 --> 00:12:45,062
Wow!

169
00:12:45,271 --> 00:12:47,521
- It's really tall, man.
- And pretty!

170
00:12:47,562 --> 00:12:49,396
Wow! How pretty is this!

171
00:12:49,937 --> 00:12:53,354
What are you doing?
Use a spoon, at least.

172
00:12:53,437 --> 00:12:54,437
You have to try it.

173
00:12:59,896 --> 00:13:02,187
- Happy anniversary.
- Happy anniversary.

174
00:13:04,646 --> 00:13:06,312
Mmm... Yummy.

175
00:13:09,021 --> 00:13:10,187
Can we eat it all?

176
00:13:15,062 --> 00:13:16,062
Thank you.

177
00:13:24,312 --> 00:13:25,312
Rohan.

178
00:13:25,812 --> 00:13:27,312
Come.
Food is ready.

179
00:13:27,396 --> 00:13:28,271
Okay.

180
00:13:28,312 --> 00:13:31,729
- Ask my dad about the leather jacket.
- Arun, you too.

181
00:13:32,896 --> 00:13:34,646
Why are you
pulling his leg, Sohrab?

182
00:13:35,062 --> 00:13:37,229
- It's very stylish.
- Correct.

183
00:13:37,312 --> 00:13:39,896
- I've had it since Second World War.
- Second World War!

184
00:13:39,937 --> 00:13:42,646
- He's jumping down.
- Got it myself from Sarojini Nagar.

185
00:13:42,771 --> 00:13:44,604
You don't get it in that market.

186
00:13:44,646 --> 00:13:47,229
Sohrab, you're awful.

187
00:13:48,271 --> 00:13:49,437
They latch on whenever
they see an opening.

188
00:13:49,521 --> 00:13:51,812
- What's Sarojini Nagar?
- It's a market in Delhi.

189
00:13:51,896 --> 00:13:55,312
Second World War, my foot! He
took it off a dead soldier's body.

190
00:13:55,437 --> 00:13:57,104
- Please shut up.
- Rohan, sit here.

191
00:13:57,187 --> 00:13:59,896
- Doc, can you serve Arun please?
- Yeah, sure.

192
00:13:59,937 --> 00:14:01,187
Sohrab, stop it.

193
00:14:01,937 --> 00:14:03,312
You can't tease your father.

194
00:14:04,812 --> 00:14:06,021
- Baba?
- Jayanti...

195
00:14:06,646 --> 00:14:08,562
- Isn't this your sweater?
- Yeah.

196
00:14:08,812 --> 00:14:11,521
Hey, why are you
in your wife's sweater?

197
00:14:11,521 --> 00:14:14,104
So, what?
I wear his shirts too.

198
00:14:14,187 --> 00:14:15,896
Didn't you bring your own?

199
00:14:15,937 --> 00:14:18,396
So, the two of you
went to the same college?

200
00:14:18,521 --> 00:14:20,562
Me, no.
I was with Raman's brother.

201
00:14:20,687 --> 00:14:21,687
Oh, okay.

202
00:14:21,771 --> 00:14:23,521
Both studied science.

203
00:14:24,187 --> 00:14:27,937
He studied medicine,
psycho-analysis, all that jazz.

204
00:14:28,062 --> 00:14:29,687
Oh wow!

205
00:14:29,771 --> 00:14:31,271
Oh, you're one of those doctors!

206
00:14:31,562 --> 00:14:32,979
You treat the retards.

207
00:14:33,062 --> 00:14:35,187
- You can't say these things.
- No. I don't treat them.

208
00:14:35,271 --> 00:14:36,812
The patients
have to treat themselves.

209
00:14:37,437 --> 00:14:39,396
- You must prescribe medicines.
- No.

210
00:14:39,396 --> 00:14:40,937
Your friend is such a fake doctor?

211
00:14:41,021 --> 00:14:42,896
Doesn't treat anyone.
Doesn't prescribe meds.

212
00:14:42,937 --> 00:14:44,521
So, you give them a massage?

213
00:14:46,437 --> 00:14:48,021
Actually, I just point the way.

214
00:14:48,146 --> 00:14:51,021
I watch, I listen.
And somehow that seems to help.

215
00:14:51,396 --> 00:14:52,812
Like our homeopathy doctors.

216
00:14:52,937 --> 00:14:55,271
They can diagnose just by feeling
the pulse.

217
00:14:55,354 --> 00:14:56,354
Something like that.

218
00:14:56,562 --> 00:14:58,812
The pulse I feel is words.
Words reveal, you know.

219
00:14:58,937 --> 00:15:00,021
He can look into your soul.

220
00:15:00,146 --> 00:15:01,896
Don't make eye contact
with the doc.

221
00:15:01,896 --> 00:15:02,896
Are you serious?

222
00:15:03,146 --> 00:15:04,521
And he charges money for that.

223
00:15:04,562 --> 00:15:06,146
Don't scare everyone away.

224
00:15:06,271 --> 00:15:07,646
This is a good business.

225
00:15:07,771 --> 00:15:09,896
- Easy street.
- He's very famous.

226
00:15:10,062 --> 00:15:11,062
Google him.

227
00:15:11,771 --> 00:15:13,146
I've already googled him.

228
00:15:14,521 --> 00:15:16,146
- Isn't it good?
- Yeah.

229
00:15:16,437 --> 00:15:17,646
It's good, is it?

230
00:15:18,437 --> 00:15:19,687
- Sure?
- It's good.

231
00:15:20,271 --> 00:15:21,521
Isn't the salt a little less?

232
00:15:22,312 --> 00:15:24,729
- Maybe a little.
- I knew you were too shy to say it.

233
00:15:24,937 --> 00:15:26,312
- It seems fine to me.
- Add some salt.

234
00:15:26,437 --> 00:15:27,437
It's okay.

235
00:15:27,521 --> 00:15:29,437
- Why don't you eat?
- It's just salt, man.

236
00:15:29,521 --> 00:15:32,021
- Have some roti.
- Try it.

237
00:15:32,062 --> 00:15:34,021
- Sohrab, let it be.
- Here.

238
00:15:34,771 --> 00:15:35,937
Come on.

239
00:15:36,271 --> 00:15:39,187
- Sohrab, let him be.
- Can't eat without salt, my love.

240
00:15:39,771 --> 00:15:40,646
Here you go.

241
00:15:40,771 --> 00:15:42,312
It's just salt, kiddo.
You need it.

242
00:15:43,896 --> 00:15:44,896
Now try it.

243
00:15:45,396 --> 00:15:46,396
Go ahead.

244
00:15:49,562 --> 00:15:50,687
- Better now?
- Better.

245
00:15:50,771 --> 00:15:52,812
Isn't it?
You're not doing it right.

246
00:15:52,937 --> 00:15:55,312
What are you doing?

247
00:15:55,396 --> 00:15:56,396
What are you doing?

248
00:15:56,437 --> 00:15:57,646
Jayanti, say something.

249
00:15:57,687 --> 00:15:58,646
- Sohrab!
- Mix it well.

250
00:15:58,687 --> 00:15:59,771
Shut up!
Eat your food.

251
00:16:01,562 --> 00:16:02,646
Mix it.

252
00:16:04,396 --> 00:16:05,771
Here you go.
Now give it a taste.

253
00:16:07,937 --> 00:16:09,062
- Isn't it better now?
- Much better.

254
00:16:09,687 --> 00:16:10,687
Great!

255
00:16:10,937 --> 00:16:12,437
I love you, Sandeep.

256
00:16:12,896 --> 00:16:15,187
Doc, forget about Canada
and come back.

257
00:16:15,271 --> 00:16:16,271
You'll earn a lot of money.

258
00:16:16,396 --> 00:16:17,562
You should know when to stop.

259
00:16:17,854 --> 00:16:18,937
Sometimes you really cross the line.

260
00:16:19,021 --> 00:16:20,187
This is nothing.

261
00:16:20,396 --> 00:16:24,437
If I'd put in half a bowl,
he'd still eat it. Right, Sandy?

262
00:16:24,521 --> 00:16:26,437
- I would.
- Tell that to your wife.

263
00:16:26,521 --> 00:16:27,937
Give me your bowl.

264
00:16:32,271 --> 00:16:34,146
- Can I get a roti?
- Yeah.

265
00:16:40,521 --> 00:16:41,521
Yes, sir.

266
00:16:42,312 --> 00:16:44,896
-Alright, so who called?
-I did, Raman Chawla.

267
00:16:45,146 --> 00:16:46,437
Are you Inspector Aditya?

268
00:16:46,771 --> 00:16:48,896
No, sir is busy.
He'll come later.

269
00:16:49,021 --> 00:16:50,312
For now,
you can talk to us.

270
00:16:51,396 --> 00:16:52,479
Who is the victim?

271
00:16:52,812 --> 00:16:54,437
Sohrab Handa, our friend.

272
00:16:54,687 --> 00:16:55,687
Who killed him?

273
00:16:58,646 --> 00:17:01,312
We're cops.
You can trust us.

274
00:17:01,396 --> 00:17:02,396
Tell us.

275
00:17:02,646 --> 00:17:04,021
Sir, we were asleep.

276
00:17:05,271 --> 00:17:07,021
We were sleeping too.

277
00:17:07,896 --> 00:17:09,271
Come along, Amar ji.

278
00:17:25,646 --> 00:17:26,896
Get her out of here.

279
00:17:30,062 --> 00:17:31,062
Ma'am.

280
00:17:31,646 --> 00:17:33,021
Ma'am, if you could step aside...

281
00:17:33,687 --> 00:17:35,187
He isn't well.

282
00:17:35,562 --> 00:17:37,021
So, I will have to be here...

283
00:17:41,396 --> 00:17:42,354
Isha.

284
00:17:44,021 --> 00:17:45,396
He's not well, Suman.

285
00:17:45,396 --> 00:17:47,187
- She's his wife.
- I'll stay here. Okay?

286
00:17:48,646 --> 00:17:50,396
- Just...
- He's not well.

287
00:17:50,437 --> 00:17:51,437
It's fine.

288
00:17:54,687 --> 00:17:57,187
- What's his name?
- Sohrab Handa.

289
00:17:58,812 --> 00:18:01,812
- How is he related to you?
- He was my business partner.

290
00:18:02,687 --> 00:18:04,271
- Your business partner?
- Yes.

291
00:18:05,896 --> 00:18:06,771
- Amar ji?
- Yes, sir.

292
00:18:07,437 --> 00:18:09,396
- You've got the plastic bags?
- Yes.

293
00:18:09,437 --> 00:18:10,521
Whatever you find...

294
00:18:11,021 --> 00:18:12,062
Keep it in the bags.

295
00:18:12,521 --> 00:18:14,146
All of you, listen carefully.

296
00:18:14,896 --> 00:18:18,271
Nobody touches anything.
It's all evidence.

297
00:18:18,396 --> 00:18:19,521
- Got it?
- Yes.

298
00:18:19,521 --> 00:18:20,479
Got it...

299
00:18:20,896 --> 00:18:21,812
What's going on?

300
00:18:22,896 --> 00:18:25,021
Didn't you hear what I said?

301
00:18:25,562 --> 00:18:26,896
Cigarette...

302
00:18:26,937 --> 00:18:27,937
Sandeep.

303
00:18:29,187 --> 00:18:30,396
- Arun!
- Amar ji.

304
00:18:30,771 --> 00:18:32,812
- Put this in evidence.
- Arun!

305
00:18:33,312 --> 00:18:36,896
- Take his number.
- Get a blanket for your brother.

306
00:18:38,271 --> 00:18:39,521
It's getting chilly.

307
00:18:40,187 --> 00:18:41,437
Did you hear me?

308
00:18:42,812 --> 00:18:46,146
Who was the first one

309
00:18:47,771 --> 00:18:48,896
to see the body?

310
00:18:51,646 --> 00:18:52,937
I did.

311
00:18:54,771 --> 00:18:55,771
What's your name?

312
00:18:56,021 --> 00:18:57,771
Jayanti.
She's my wife.

313
00:18:58,021 --> 00:19:00,687
Jayanti ji, he's asking you.
Tell him your name.

314
00:19:02,021 --> 00:19:03,271
My name is Jayanti.

315
00:19:03,521 --> 00:19:06,187
Amar ji, note down 'Jayanti'.

316
00:19:06,687 --> 00:19:08,062
Go on...

317
00:19:09,437 --> 00:19:13,312
I came here to get some water
at around 12:30.

318
00:19:13,396 --> 00:19:14,562
That's when I saw him.

319
00:19:15,437 --> 00:19:16,437
I see.

320
00:19:17,521 --> 00:19:18,771
You were here at 12:30.

321
00:19:19,562 --> 00:19:20,687
And...

322
00:19:20,771 --> 00:19:22,812
Who was the last person
who saw him?

323
00:19:22,896 --> 00:19:23,854
I did, sir.

324
00:19:23,937 --> 00:19:24,937
- Alive?
- Yes.

325
00:19:25,021 --> 00:19:26,312
- Your name?
- Madhvan.

326
00:19:26,646 --> 00:19:27,646
Madhvan.

327
00:19:28,937 --> 00:19:30,771
What did you see, Madhvan ji?

328
00:19:31,687 --> 00:19:34,771
It was around 12 and I

329
00:19:35,312 --> 00:19:37,312
was here for some cake. And...

330
00:19:37,771 --> 00:19:38,771
Sohrab

331
00:19:38,854 --> 00:19:40,354
- was seated on this very chair...
- Hey!

332
00:19:40,437 --> 00:19:43,229
Look who's here!

333
00:19:43,312 --> 00:19:44,646
Can't believe it's you!

334
00:19:44,771 --> 00:19:47,021
- Recognise him?
- I'm a huge fan.

335
00:19:47,146 --> 00:19:49,271
- He's from the show "Pardafaash".
- Right.

336
00:19:49,562 --> 00:19:51,562
Kumar ji, this is amazing!

337
00:19:52,437 --> 00:19:53,687
Put it on your brother.

338
00:19:54,812 --> 00:19:57,146
Do I need to spell everything out?

339
00:19:59,562 --> 00:20:01,521
Have both of you lost it?

340
00:20:02,312 --> 00:20:03,562
Take it away.

341
00:20:04,021 --> 00:20:05,229
My child...

342
00:20:06,187 --> 00:20:08,187
He doesn't need any of this now.

343
00:20:08,271 --> 00:20:10,396
He'll fall ill, Baba.

344
00:20:10,521 --> 00:20:13,021
Then, we'll have to
take him to the doctor.

345
00:20:13,521 --> 00:20:14,937
Vijaya, explain it to him.

346
00:20:15,896 --> 00:20:16,896
Ma'am...

347
00:20:18,271 --> 00:20:19,271
Ma'am.

348
00:20:21,312 --> 00:20:22,437
He won't get up now.

349
00:20:25,646 --> 00:20:27,312
- Isha!
- Isha! Stop it.

350
00:20:27,437 --> 00:20:29,146
How dare you?

351
00:20:29,271 --> 00:20:30,687
- How dare you?
- Stop.

352
00:20:30,771 --> 00:20:33,021
Isha...

353
00:20:33,146 --> 00:20:34,146
Stop!

354
00:20:34,396 --> 00:20:35,396
- Stop it.
- Isha...

355
00:20:35,521 --> 00:20:37,687
- Stop it!
- Isha!

356
00:20:37,937 --> 00:20:40,562
Just shut up!

357
00:20:40,812 --> 00:20:42,062
Isha...Calm down.

358
00:20:42,562 --> 00:20:44,187
That's enough.

359
00:20:46,187 --> 00:20:47,396
Stop...

360
00:21:15,021 --> 00:21:16,021
Some tea?

361
00:21:20,437 --> 00:21:21,437
Tea?

362
00:21:27,896 --> 00:21:29,021
Is the sugar okay?

363
00:21:41,771 --> 00:21:43,312
I need to get the injection...

364
00:21:43,687 --> 00:21:44,687
For Baba.

365
00:21:53,312 --> 00:21:55,854
You know about ma'am, right?

366
00:21:56,771 --> 00:21:57,687
What?

367
00:21:58,062 --> 00:21:59,854
She walks in her sleep.

368
00:22:03,646 --> 00:22:04,771
Sleepwalking.

369
00:22:17,062 --> 00:22:18,062
Are you okay?

370
00:22:18,771 --> 00:22:19,771
- Yeah.
- Hmm.

371
00:22:20,062 --> 00:22:21,271
Don't be scared.

372
00:22:23,021 --> 00:22:24,437
Why would I be scared?

373
00:22:26,271 --> 00:22:27,646
You didn't do it, right?

374
00:22:30,312 --> 00:22:31,437
Of course not.

375
00:22:32,271 --> 00:22:33,521
Then I don't care.

376
00:22:40,646 --> 00:22:42,396
From here to here...

377
00:22:42,687 --> 00:22:45,812
in one brutal move!

378
00:22:46,521 --> 00:22:48,146
With something very sharp.

379
00:22:48,271 --> 00:22:49,771
- What?
- The knife is not here.

380
00:22:49,771 --> 00:22:53,896
You mean like a blade or a knife.

381
00:22:55,021 --> 00:22:57,979
- The cake knife is not here.
- How can that be?

382
00:22:58,062 --> 00:23:00,021
- It's missing.
- I left it right here.

383
00:23:00,062 --> 00:23:01,021
Not there, now.

384
00:23:01,896 --> 00:23:03,562
Whose birthday was it?

385
00:23:03,771 --> 00:23:06,062
Not a birthday.

386
00:23:07,021 --> 00:23:08,729
It was our wedding anniversary.

387
00:23:08,854 --> 00:23:09,771
I see.

388
00:23:09,896 --> 00:23:10,896
Happy anniversary.

389
00:23:11,687 --> 00:23:15,021
But this wasn't done
with a cake knife.

390
00:23:15,396 --> 00:23:16,396
No!

391
00:23:16,562 --> 00:23:19,771
Actually, it was a big knife.

392
00:23:21,521 --> 00:23:24,021
To cut meat.

393
00:23:25,312 --> 00:23:26,479
Is that what you used?

394
00:23:27,271 --> 00:23:29,021
To cut the cake, yes.

395
00:23:29,646 --> 00:23:30,771
What does he mean?

396
00:23:30,937 --> 00:23:32,146
And now it's missing.

397
00:23:33,187 --> 00:23:34,312
Where did you keep it?

398
00:23:35,312 --> 00:23:36,312
What do you mean?

399
00:23:37,021 --> 00:23:40,396
I mean you must have hidden
the knife after slitting his throat.

400
00:23:40,437 --> 00:23:41,771
So, where did you hide it?

401
00:23:43,396 --> 00:23:45,146
You think I did it?

402
00:23:45,521 --> 00:23:49,312
- That I killed my friend?
- You're one who called the cops.

403
00:23:49,437 --> 00:23:51,104
Because that's
the right thing to do.

404
00:23:51,187 --> 00:23:53,104
Have to call the police.

405
00:23:53,187 --> 00:23:55,187
We'll figure it out at the station.
Get him along.

406
00:23:55,229 --> 00:23:56,271
- Let's go.
- No...

407
00:23:56,396 --> 00:23:57,687
- What do you mean?
- Move aside.

408
00:23:57,771 --> 00:23:58,979
What's going on?
Come on.

409
00:23:59,062 --> 00:24:00,521
- Your cake. Your knife.
- Sit here.

410
00:24:00,604 --> 00:24:01,229
So what?

411
00:24:01,312 --> 00:24:02,771
- You're the one who called.
- Just because I called you,

412
00:24:02,812 --> 00:24:04,312
I'm the killer?

413
00:24:04,437 --> 00:24:06,812
Madam, put your phone off.

414
00:24:06,937 --> 00:24:09,646
- Talk to him.
- We're trying to do our work.

415
00:24:09,687 --> 00:24:11,062
Give me the phone.

416
00:24:11,187 --> 00:24:13,771
You can't just use your phone.
We're inquiring.

417
00:24:13,771 --> 00:24:15,146
Just answer the phone.

418
00:24:15,187 --> 00:24:17,021
- Hello?
- We're trying to work here.

419
00:24:17,062 --> 00:24:18,521
- Just let us.
- Go ahead.

420
00:24:21,646 --> 00:24:22,812
- Who is it?
- Boss.

421
00:24:24,562 --> 00:24:25,812
Yes, sir.

422
00:24:26,437 --> 00:24:29,604
No, sir.
Just regular inquiry.

423
00:24:30,271 --> 00:24:33,604
No, sir...
Nothing till you get here...

424
00:24:33,687 --> 00:24:35,396
Don't know what
he's trying to imply.

425
00:24:35,396 --> 00:24:37,646
We'd just take their statements.

426
00:24:38,271 --> 00:24:41,021
We'll find out what happened.
Rest assured, sir..

427
00:24:41,896 --> 00:24:42,896
You spoke to him?

428
00:24:44,396 --> 00:24:45,646
Why would you do that?

429
00:24:46,771 --> 00:24:48,646
- My phone?
- He'll keep it.

430
00:24:48,687 --> 00:24:51,271
- Why?
- You can't make calls like this.

431
00:24:51,396 --> 00:24:55,729
- Please don't talk disrespectfully.
- How am I being disrespectful?

432
00:24:55,812 --> 00:24:57,021
Nena...

433
00:24:57,146 --> 00:24:59,437
- Give us the room.
- Don't raise your voice.

434
00:24:59,521 --> 00:25:01,271
- Let us do our job.
- Please go ahead.

435
00:25:01,396 --> 00:25:03,812
- It's my earnest request.
- Show some respect.

436
00:25:04,021 --> 00:25:05,771
Then I will talk to you.

437
00:25:05,771 --> 00:25:06,896
Come with me.

438
00:25:08,521 --> 00:25:09,937
- Kumar ji?
- Yes?

439
00:25:09,937 --> 00:25:12,104
- Can I have a minute?
- You don't have to talk...

440
00:25:12,687 --> 00:25:14,937
Madam, please wait.
It won't take long.

441
00:25:15,562 --> 00:25:16,812
This way, sir.

442
00:25:17,021 --> 00:25:19,062
Kumar, don't say anything
without a lawyer.

443
00:25:20,021 --> 00:25:21,021
Yeah, so...

444
00:25:22,687 --> 00:25:25,021
Now, tell me. In detail.

445
00:25:26,812 --> 00:25:29,771
Everything that happened
since you got here.

446
00:25:31,062 --> 00:25:34,229
We got here around 3:30.

447
00:25:34,646 --> 00:25:36,271
We got late
because we were recording.

448
00:25:37,021 --> 00:25:38,937
When we got here,
the party was in full swing.

449
00:25:39,521 --> 00:25:40,479
Hey, Jayanti.

450
00:25:40,521 --> 00:25:42,271
- How are you?
- I'm good.

451
00:25:42,312 --> 00:25:44,146
- Happy anniversary.
- Thank you. Is this for me?

452
00:25:44,312 --> 00:25:45,479
Of course. Who else?

453
00:25:45,562 --> 00:25:46,562
I'll have all of it.

454
00:25:46,937 --> 00:25:48,187
Hey, Isha.

455
00:25:48,187 --> 00:25:49,104
Hi!

456
00:25:49,146 --> 00:25:50,937
You look more handsome
in real life.

457
00:25:51,062 --> 00:25:53,521
Thank you so much.

458
00:25:54,187 --> 00:25:56,146
Absolutely.
We have to party tonight.

459
00:25:57,271 --> 00:25:58,646
- How are you, Sandeep?
- Very well.

460
00:25:59,521 --> 00:26:01,937
- Okay.
- I'm too excited.

461
00:26:02,312 --> 00:26:06,562
- Are we the last ones here?
- Madhvan is still to come.

462
00:26:06,646 --> 00:26:09,979
You know how he is.
Has to make a stylish entry.

463
00:26:10,062 --> 00:26:12,021
Hey, Raman. My friend!

464
00:26:12,521 --> 00:26:14,021
- Superstar.
- Happy anniversary.

465
00:26:14,437 --> 00:26:16,771
- You survived ten years?
- Feels like 300.

466
00:26:18,146 --> 00:26:19,812
I did. Managed.

467
00:26:19,937 --> 00:26:21,146
Handa!

468
00:26:21,812 --> 00:26:22,687
How are you you, hero?

469
00:26:22,812 --> 00:26:24,521
- How are you?
- Very well. Thank you.

470
00:26:24,562 --> 00:26:26,437
- Congratulations!
- Thank you.

471
00:26:27,062 --> 00:26:28,687
Kumar, meet Dr Chandra.

472
00:26:28,771 --> 00:26:29,771
- Hi.
- Hi.

473
00:26:29,896 --> 00:26:31,771
Dr Chandra. Kumar, Nena.

474
00:26:31,812 --> 00:26:32,937
- Hi, Nena.
- Hello, Doctor.

475
00:26:33,021 --> 00:26:34,146
Just Chandra.
I'm not a doctor.

476
00:26:34,937 --> 00:26:35,896
Hey.

477
00:26:36,687 --> 00:26:37,812
Of course, he's a doctor.

478
00:26:37,896 --> 00:26:39,521
And he's come all the way
from Canada.

479
00:26:40,687 --> 00:26:42,521
Shall we step out for a bit?

480
00:26:42,646 --> 00:26:44,854
- Their crap will continue. Come on.
- I was already in Bangalore.

481
00:26:44,937 --> 00:26:47,062
But I did come from Bangalore
for your party.

482
00:26:47,187 --> 00:26:48,812
You have such loyal friends, Raman.

483
00:26:48,812 --> 00:26:52,062
That's saying something about him.
And Jayanti.

484
00:26:52,187 --> 00:26:54,062
- Baba!
- Look who's here.

485
00:26:54,687 --> 00:26:56,104
"Pardafaash!"

486
00:26:57,396 --> 00:26:58,937
- Good to see you.
- Please sit.

487
00:26:59,062 --> 00:27:01,271
- Hi, Suman.
- Hi!

488
00:27:01,396 --> 00:27:03,437
- Hello, uncle. How are you?
- Hi. How are you?

489
00:27:03,896 --> 00:27:06,687
Sandeep is your biggest fan.
Biggest!

490
00:27:08,187 --> 00:27:10,562
Will you record today's episode
from here?

491
00:27:10,646 --> 00:27:12,771
No, I've already recorded it.
That's why we got late.

492
00:27:12,812 --> 00:27:15,021
- We've recorded it, Baba.
- So, it's not live?

493
00:27:15,021 --> 00:27:17,146
Can't go live every day.
Not possible.

494
00:27:17,271 --> 00:27:18,271
That's cheating.

495
00:27:18,396 --> 00:27:23,062
It's been one hell of a hectic ride
for the last eight months.

496
00:27:23,146 --> 00:27:24,687
She is a slave driver.

497
00:27:24,771 --> 00:27:27,646
Hello, your life has changed
in the past eight months.

498
00:27:27,687 --> 00:27:30,396
The world has changed.
People's attitude has changed.

499
00:27:30,396 --> 00:27:31,937
Working like a slave.

500
00:27:38,312 --> 00:27:39,396
Do you see that tree?

501
00:27:41,396 --> 00:27:42,937
How beautiful it is.

502
00:27:46,312 --> 00:27:47,896
Who would have made it?

503
00:27:51,021 --> 00:27:52,146
One branch...

504
00:27:52,896 --> 00:27:54,271
Another one out of that.

505
00:27:55,521 --> 00:27:56,771
And another.

506
00:27:57,146 --> 00:27:58,146
And the leaves.

507
00:27:59,812 --> 00:28:01,521
And how they move, man.

508
00:28:07,062 --> 00:28:08,271
Amazing!

509
00:28:11,062 --> 00:28:13,062
What an amazing job He has done!

510
00:28:16,396 --> 00:28:18,271
Just messed up
while making humans.

511
00:28:20,687 --> 00:28:21,687
Isn't it?

512
00:28:23,562 --> 00:28:24,562
You okay?

513
00:28:25,521 --> 00:28:26,979
Hope you're not getting bored.

514
00:28:28,021 --> 00:28:30,521
Let me know if you get bored,
we'd leave.

515
00:28:34,812 --> 00:28:35,937
Cake!

516
00:28:36,312 --> 00:28:37,646
Wow!

517
00:28:37,729 --> 00:28:38,896
Wow!

518
00:28:38,896 --> 00:28:40,146
Who got this wonderful cake?

519
00:28:40,146 --> 00:28:40,771
Thank you.

520
00:28:40,812 --> 00:28:43,229
- Who got the cake?
- He did. Thank you, Chandra.

521
00:28:43,396 --> 00:28:45,437
Well done!

522
00:28:45,521 --> 00:28:46,646
Well done!

523
00:28:46,771 --> 00:28:48,021
Did you get it from Canada?

524
00:28:49,396 --> 00:28:54,062
I am not cutting it...
with a butter knife, guys, come on!

525
00:28:54,146 --> 00:28:55,437
Satya, get a proper knife.

526
00:28:55,521 --> 00:28:56,812
Jayanti, wait a minute.

527
00:28:56,896 --> 00:28:59,437
Madhvan is almost here.
He's parking his car.

528
00:28:59,562 --> 00:29:00,812
- He's here.
- Wait for me.

529
00:29:01,437 --> 00:29:03,437
I'm waiting. Just get him.

530
00:29:03,562 --> 00:29:05,021
- Wait, I'll get him.
- I am.

531
00:29:05,062 --> 00:29:06,062
Look at this.

532
00:29:06,271 --> 00:29:09,021
- Is this good enough for you guys?
- Yes.

533
00:29:10,146 --> 00:29:12,937
That's the perfect allegory
for our 10th anniversary.

534
00:29:13,062 --> 00:29:15,271
What are you going to do with it?
Cut it or stab it?

535
00:29:15,271 --> 00:29:16,271
Stab!

536
00:29:16,396 --> 00:29:18,521
That's a very good idea.

537
00:29:18,771 --> 00:29:20,396
Satya!
Madhvan is here.

538
00:29:20,437 --> 00:29:22,146
- Are they here?
- Madhvan, brother!

539
00:29:23,062 --> 00:29:24,687
Hi, Sandeep.
So sorry, man.

540
00:29:24,771 --> 00:29:26,187
- No problem.
- The GPS was confusing.

541
00:29:26,312 --> 00:29:28,479
It's okay.
You got here in time.

542
00:29:28,562 --> 00:29:29,687
This is Nazia.

543
00:29:29,771 --> 00:29:32,271
- So sorry.
- Sure, blame the GPS.

544
00:29:32,396 --> 00:29:34,521
- Hey, Maddy!
- Hey, Kumar!

545
00:29:36,562 --> 00:29:38,646
- How are you, brother?
- Good.

546
00:29:38,687 --> 00:29:40,396
- We've been stalling for you.
- Thank you.

547
00:29:40,646 --> 00:29:43,062
- Hey, how are you?
- Haven't let Raman and Handa start.

548
00:29:43,271 --> 00:29:44,521
Haven't let them cut the cake yet.

549
00:30:21,312 --> 00:30:23,271
Surprise!

550
00:30:26,479 --> 00:30:28,021
So sorry. Hope this makes up for it.

551
00:30:28,062 --> 00:30:30,104
Better be sorry.

552
00:30:30,104 --> 00:30:31,396
Better late than never.

553
00:30:31,396 --> 00:30:34,521
- Go on. Cut the cake.
- Shall we, baby?

554
00:30:34,937 --> 00:30:36,146
Okay, baby.
Here we go.

555
00:30:37,812 --> 00:30:39,021
Just cut it.

556
00:30:44,646 --> 00:30:46,521
Oh my God!

557
00:30:46,812 --> 00:30:47,812
You first.

558
00:30:47,896 --> 00:30:50,437
No. You first.

559
00:30:50,437 --> 00:30:51,812
Kiss!

560
00:30:52,229 --> 00:30:54,187
Guys, get a room.

561
00:30:54,562 --> 00:30:58,396
This day will be forever
marked as Raman-Jayanti day!

562
00:31:00,646 --> 00:31:01,937
Speech, guys!

563
00:31:02,021 --> 00:31:03,646
Okay, time for the speech, now.

564
00:31:03,687 --> 00:31:04,604
Okay.

565
00:31:04,646 --> 00:31:06,187
I've not prepared this.

566
00:31:06,521 --> 00:31:07,521
I have actually.

567
00:31:09,021 --> 00:31:10,562
I've got two words to say.

568
00:31:11,271 --> 00:31:12,771
Fudge you for coming late.

569
00:31:15,062 --> 00:31:15,896
He's just saying it.

570
00:31:15,937 --> 00:31:17,854
But seriously, Jayanti...

571
00:31:18,812 --> 00:31:22,146
Without you,
none of this would be possible.

572
00:31:22,271 --> 00:31:25,187
So thank you
for rocking up into this world.

573
00:31:25,396 --> 00:31:27,396
Thank you for accepting me.

574
00:31:27,437 --> 00:31:28,896
And dealing with me.

575
00:31:29,396 --> 00:31:30,396
And for being you.

576
00:31:30,437 --> 00:31:31,937
He is such a schmoozer!

577
00:31:33,021 --> 00:31:34,521
He's a smooth operator.

578
00:31:34,646 --> 00:31:36,854
- How's that?
- Your turn.

579
00:31:36,937 --> 00:31:38,896
- Jayanti, your turn now.
- Come on.

580
00:31:39,062 --> 00:31:40,146
Your turn.

581
00:31:40,187 --> 00:31:41,187
Okay...

582
00:31:42,312 --> 00:31:45,479
When we met 10 years ago...

583
00:31:46,271 --> 00:31:48,896
It's been 10 years, Raman.
I can't believe it to begin with.

584
00:31:50,521 --> 00:31:53,896
I guess it was a leap of faith
as all marriages are.

585
00:31:54,521 --> 00:31:56,312
And yet, here we are.

586
00:31:56,437 --> 00:31:57,771
- Yeah. We're here.
- Yeah.

587
00:31:58,021 --> 00:31:59,021
Cheers to that!

588
00:31:59,062 --> 00:32:02,771
You know how they say
it takes a village to raise a child.

589
00:32:03,437 --> 00:32:06,312
I really think it takes a village
to raise a marriage.

590
00:32:06,687 --> 00:32:07,937
I really do.

591
00:32:08,937 --> 00:32:10,229
And...and...

592
00:32:10,437 --> 00:32:13,562
For us, you all are that village.

593
00:32:13,771 --> 00:32:15,646
- And--
- Are you calling us villagers?

594
00:32:16,521 --> 00:32:18,396
You're definitely a villager.

595
00:32:18,437 --> 00:32:20,771
- She's saying such nice things.
- I know.

596
00:32:20,937 --> 00:32:22,896
But I really mean it.
Thank you for being there.

597
00:32:23,021 --> 00:32:23,646
I...

598
00:32:23,771 --> 00:32:26,146
- We wouldn't have it any other way.
- True.

599
00:32:26,271 --> 00:32:27,062
Can we eat the cake now?

600
00:32:27,146 --> 00:32:29,062
Have the cake but don't finish it.

601
00:32:31,771 --> 00:32:32,771
Congratulations.

602
00:32:33,771 --> 00:32:34,771
Love you, guys.

603
00:32:34,896 --> 00:32:35,896
Get the glasses.

604
00:32:37,396 --> 00:32:38,312
Don't drink from the bottle.

605
00:32:38,396 --> 00:32:40,062
- Okay, let's cut the cake.
- Guys, guys.

606
00:32:40,146 --> 00:32:40,896
Congratulations!

607
00:32:41,146 --> 00:32:41,896
This is Nazia.

608
00:32:42,021 --> 00:32:43,271
- Nazia, this is the gang.
- Hi.

609
00:32:43,271 --> 00:32:44,562
- Hi.
- Hello.

610
00:32:44,771 --> 00:32:45,937
- Hi.
- Nazia, sorry.

611
00:32:46,021 --> 00:32:48,562
Nazia, be careful
of these intellectual types.

612
00:32:48,812 --> 00:32:50,062
He is all hollow on the inside.

613
00:32:50,187 --> 00:32:51,812
That's my good friend,
Sohrab Handa.

614
00:32:52,062 --> 00:32:53,396
You're lucky that I'm your friend.

615
00:32:53,521 --> 00:32:55,271
And not your enemy.

616
00:32:55,312 --> 00:32:57,312
Forget it, Handa.
With you, it's all the same.

617
00:32:57,396 --> 00:32:58,396
Here we go again.

618
00:32:58,396 --> 00:32:59,562
Where's your beautiful wife?
Isha!

619
00:32:59,646 --> 00:33:00,646
I'm here.

620
00:33:00,687 --> 00:33:02,812
Year after year, I wonder...

621
00:33:02,896 --> 00:33:04,896
How do you keep living
with this Neanderthal?

622
00:33:04,937 --> 00:33:06,437
That's not for you.

623
00:33:06,521 --> 00:33:08,062
He's my Neanderthal.

624
00:33:08,396 --> 00:33:10,187
- Here.
- Enjoy the champagne.

625
00:33:10,437 --> 00:33:12,187
Spent his life drinking champagne.

626
00:33:12,271 --> 00:33:13,687
- Thank you.
- Cheers.

627
00:33:13,812 --> 00:33:15,646
Cheers, guys.
So nice to see you all.

628
00:33:16,187 --> 00:33:18,021
Can we chat for a bit?

629
00:33:18,396 --> 00:33:19,396
Now?

630
00:33:19,646 --> 00:33:20,896
Yeah.

631
00:33:21,187 --> 00:33:22,437
Sure.

632
00:33:23,521 --> 00:33:24,687
Not here, Nena.

633
00:33:28,521 --> 00:33:30,479
Am I entitled to some cake?

634
00:33:34,521 --> 00:33:35,937
So, this is what we'll do.

635
00:33:36,437 --> 00:33:37,562
You buy him out.

636
00:33:38,021 --> 00:33:39,521
Buy his shares in the company.

637
00:33:40,562 --> 00:33:42,396
He moves out.
You move in.

638
00:33:43,271 --> 00:33:44,271
Seriously?

639
00:33:44,437 --> 00:33:45,521
He'll never agree to it.

640
00:33:45,562 --> 00:33:47,771
You let me handle that.

641
00:33:48,271 --> 00:33:49,271
Yeah?

642
00:33:50,187 --> 00:33:51,187
You tell me.

643
00:33:51,646 --> 00:33:52,646
Are you in?

644
00:33:53,021 --> 00:33:54,771
How come you are so confident?

645
00:33:55,146 --> 00:33:57,396
Nena, just say it.

646
00:33:59,021 --> 00:34:01,146
Well, if he's out, I'm in.

647
00:34:02,646 --> 00:34:03,646
I love you.

648
00:34:05,187 --> 00:34:06,187
Yeah, right.

649
00:34:08,271 --> 00:34:09,771
Cheers to that, partner.

650
00:34:09,812 --> 00:34:10,812
Ladies...

651
00:34:11,021 --> 00:34:12,396
So, you know her father?

652
00:34:12,437 --> 00:34:13,437
You are her father's friend?

653
00:34:13,521 --> 00:34:14,521
Isha.

654
00:34:15,521 --> 00:34:17,396
-Do you want some?
-Give me a small one.

655
00:34:17,521 --> 00:34:20,021
'Give me a small one',
says the tipsy man.'

656
00:34:20,146 --> 00:34:22,896
Daddy-o will be the first one
to get drunk.

657
00:34:23,021 --> 00:34:25,271
- Stop talking nonsense.
- He won't change.

658
00:34:26,021 --> 00:34:27,604
- This is the last one.
- What nonsense?

659
00:34:27,687 --> 00:34:28,646
No more for you.

660
00:34:28,771 --> 00:34:31,396
- Sadia is an actress too.
- Oh really?

661
00:34:31,437 --> 00:34:32,437
It's Nazia.

662
00:34:32,521 --> 00:34:35,937
No wonder you look so familiar.

663
00:34:36,021 --> 00:34:38,187
Tell us Sadia baby,
which films you're in.

664
00:34:38,521 --> 00:34:41,021
- It's Nazia!
- I'm not good with names. So what?

665
00:34:41,062 --> 00:34:42,646
- It's Nazia.
-Tell us.

666
00:34:43,312 --> 00:34:45,937
I've done a few ads...
For now, yeah.

667
00:34:46,271 --> 00:34:48,687
- Right... Ads.
- Something we might have seen?

668
00:34:48,937 --> 00:34:51,729
There's a lot of
struggle in this field.

669
00:34:51,812 --> 00:34:55,021
Our friend, Kumar,
also struggled a lot for 15 years..

670
00:34:55,062 --> 00:34:57,687
He used to beg for smokes.

671
00:34:57,812 --> 00:35:00,146
Now, look at him.
Hosts his own show in a jacket.

672
00:35:00,187 --> 00:35:01,687
Don't jinx it, bro.

673
00:35:01,937 --> 00:35:04,021
We used to smoke a lot together.

674
00:35:04,146 --> 00:35:08,271
You're so aggressive on your show.
You don't let anyone speak.

675
00:35:08,896 --> 00:35:10,854
You're not like that in real life.

676
00:35:10,937 --> 00:35:13,937
That's part of the performance.
Public demands high pitched drama.

677
00:35:14,062 --> 00:35:15,437
We have to dish it out.

678
00:35:15,562 --> 00:35:16,771
That's acting.
That's not me.

679
00:35:16,896 --> 00:35:19,812
- Is this you?
- I should think so.

680
00:35:20,812 --> 00:35:23,271
What about the stand
you take on the show?

681
00:35:23,646 --> 00:35:25,812
- Well, that helps with the TRP.
- Exactly.

682
00:35:25,896 --> 00:35:27,021
- Are you serious?
- Money, money, money.

683
00:35:27,396 --> 00:35:28,396
Guilty.

684
00:35:29,187 --> 00:35:32,646
Suman, let's say
you make bush shirts.

685
00:35:32,812 --> 00:35:34,562
No, I'm making mutton.

686
00:35:36,771 --> 00:35:37,521
Good one.

687
00:35:37,646 --> 00:35:40,021
Let's assume
that you make bush shirts.

688
00:35:40,896 --> 00:35:42,646
But the customer wants to be naked.

689
00:35:42,771 --> 00:35:43,896
Pardon my language.

690
00:35:44,021 --> 00:35:45,021
What are you going to do?

691
00:35:45,062 --> 00:35:47,146
Can't force him
to wear the bush shirt.

692
00:35:47,271 --> 00:35:50,687
- You sell what the customer wants.
- I don't buy that. That's very wrong.

693
00:35:50,896 --> 00:35:52,896
If you don't like it,
don't watch it.

694
00:35:52,896 --> 00:35:55,187
- Don't watch it.
- We'll give you more choices.

695
00:35:55,312 --> 00:35:56,771
He's not selling it to you anyway.

696
00:35:56,771 --> 00:35:59,062
- Democracy.
- It's not about me but everybody.

697
00:35:59,187 --> 00:36:01,812
Everyone should have their beliefs,
their moral code.

698
00:36:01,812 --> 00:36:04,521
Gone are those days!

699
00:36:04,562 --> 00:36:06,646
When the world
ran on principles.

700
00:36:07,021 --> 00:36:09,437
Now they are all opportunists!

701
00:36:09,521 --> 00:36:12,271
- Just thinking of profits.
- Exactly. I agree with that.

702
00:36:12,312 --> 00:36:14,729
Bravo, Daddy-o!

703
00:36:14,812 --> 00:36:16,104
Amazing thought!

704
00:36:16,396 --> 00:36:17,271
Wow!

705
00:36:17,396 --> 00:36:20,646
My dad just slayed irony.

706
00:36:21,146 --> 00:36:24,396
When his dad died,
he told me...

707
00:36:24,521 --> 00:36:27,146
That's your grandfather.
You should perform the last rites.

708
00:36:27,187 --> 00:36:28,521
Shave your head.

709
00:36:28,646 --> 00:36:30,562
Don't want my image spoilt.

710
00:36:30,687 --> 00:36:33,521
And now he is talking of principles!
Drink up!

711
00:36:34,146 --> 00:36:35,312
Bloody fraud!

712
00:36:46,812 --> 00:36:47,896
You know, Baba...

713
00:36:48,646 --> 00:36:50,812
Ideology doesn't work anymore.

714
00:36:51,437 --> 00:36:53,271
Have to sell what
the customers want.

715
00:36:53,312 --> 00:36:54,729
We're stuck.

716
00:36:55,062 --> 00:36:57,854
So, we're selling what we have to.
Sometimes it's matches or oil.

717
00:36:57,937 --> 00:37:00,729
- Sometimes, it's news.
- Go, sell it all.

718
00:37:00,812 --> 00:37:02,646
We have sold everything.

719
00:37:02,771 --> 00:37:04,062
What's left to sell, anyway?

720
00:37:04,812 --> 00:37:06,271
We have even sold our souls.

721
00:37:06,437 --> 00:37:08,312
We've become morally bankrupt.

722
00:37:08,896 --> 00:37:11,146
I don't mean you.
I mean society as a whole.

723
00:37:11,271 --> 00:37:12,937
The terrorist has dropped a bomb!

724
00:37:14,062 --> 00:37:16,396
You're the biggest fraud
of them all.

725
00:37:16,562 --> 00:37:18,312
You and your entire community.

726
00:37:18,437 --> 00:37:19,646
Your Socrates...

727
00:37:19,771 --> 00:37:24,146
What's his name, Emanuelle Kant.
Your Plato, Pluto... Sartre...

728
00:37:24,271 --> 00:37:26,854
Your Nietzsche.
All frauds.

729
00:37:27,562 --> 00:37:31,021
They are not just mine,
they belong to you too.

730
00:37:31,146 --> 00:37:32,146
I've nothing to do with them.

731
00:37:32,187 --> 00:37:33,812
By the way, you know a lot.

732
00:37:33,812 --> 00:37:35,979
Spent years
with this pretentious prick.

733
00:37:36,062 --> 00:37:37,396
Must have some effect.

734
00:37:37,437 --> 00:37:38,771
What were you saying, Maddy?

735
00:37:39,062 --> 00:37:41,312
Let it be.
He'll say I'm dropping bombs.

736
00:37:41,437 --> 00:37:43,146
- Go on, Professor.
- Go on.

737
00:37:43,187 --> 00:37:44,396
- Sohrab...
- If you stay quiet, your whiskey

738
00:37:44,437 --> 00:37:45,896
won't go down.

739
00:37:46,021 --> 00:37:47,271
This is your chance
to impress the ladies.

740
00:37:47,312 --> 00:37:48,896
It's party time!

741
00:37:48,937 --> 00:37:52,896
Show us how much you know.
If not now, then when?

742
00:37:53,437 --> 00:37:54,979
I mean, look at us.

743
00:37:56,021 --> 00:37:57,187
We were free.

744
00:37:58,062 --> 00:38:00,312
We could have achieved anything,
we were free to choose.

745
00:38:01,646 --> 00:38:03,229
And what did we choose?

746
00:38:03,312 --> 00:38:04,271
This?

747
00:38:04,646 --> 00:38:07,521
- Where did we land up?
- I think we're in a nice place.

748
00:38:07,646 --> 00:38:09,229
There's fresh air, at least.

749
00:38:09,562 --> 00:38:10,646
Suman!

750
00:38:11,896 --> 00:38:12,812
Hear that, Prof?

751
00:38:12,937 --> 00:38:14,979
- You're a cutie.
- What?

752
00:38:15,187 --> 00:38:17,271
- Isn't it true?
- It's true. I agree.

753
00:38:17,396 --> 00:38:18,521
We're truly doomed.

754
00:38:18,687 --> 00:38:19,896
You're a real pessimist.

755
00:38:20,062 --> 00:38:22,437
I feel like killing myself
right here, right now.

756
00:38:22,562 --> 00:38:24,896
On the contrary, my friend.
I'm an optimist.

757
00:38:25,187 --> 00:38:26,562
How are you an optimist?

758
00:38:26,812 --> 00:38:28,812
An optimist who thinks we're doomed?

759
00:38:28,937 --> 00:38:29,937
It's sad but true.

760
00:38:30,271 --> 00:38:32,437
Luckily, we are...

761
00:38:32,771 --> 00:38:33,812
not dead.

762
00:38:34,062 --> 00:38:37,646
I'd say we're alive.
But that'd be a gross exaggeration.

763
00:38:37,687 --> 00:38:39,687
- Professor...
- The fact that we're not dead...

764
00:38:39,812 --> 00:38:42,146
- Our messenger of doom!
- ...Is reason enough to be hopeful.

765
00:38:42,187 --> 00:38:44,271
- Professor?
- What?

766
00:38:44,437 --> 00:38:45,437
What will save us, Professor?

767
00:38:45,687 --> 00:38:47,437
- I'll tell you.
- Not asking you.

768
00:38:47,562 --> 00:38:49,937
I'll save you from this bullshit.

769
00:38:50,187 --> 00:38:52,396
- Now, keep your trap shut.
- Sohrab...

770
00:38:52,521 --> 00:38:53,687
He won't even let me speak.

771
00:38:53,812 --> 00:38:55,187
Nonstop lecture!

772
00:38:55,271 --> 00:38:57,271
Please, can you be quiet
for a minute?

773
00:38:57,437 --> 00:38:59,646
Let somebody else talk for a change.
Maddy, tell us what you think.

774
00:38:59,896 --> 00:39:00,937
Go on, Maddy.

775
00:39:02,062 --> 00:39:04,187
I was just saying that...

776
00:39:05,062 --> 00:39:07,812
As a collective,
we've all failed miserably.

777
00:39:08,187 --> 00:39:11,812
Any hope left for us
is at the individual level.

778
00:39:12,062 --> 00:39:15,312
Because as individuals
we still have some inherent goodness

779
00:39:15,521 --> 00:39:20,312
- that can pull us out of this...
- Shut up or I'll break this on you.

780
00:39:20,812 --> 00:39:22,187
Shut your trap
and make me a drink.

781
00:39:22,312 --> 00:39:24,562
I guess I was wrong
about inherent goodness.

782
00:39:25,812 --> 00:39:29,187
Move a muscle once in a while.

783
00:39:29,396 --> 00:39:31,562
Your philosophy is useless.
It's worthless.

784
00:39:31,646 --> 00:39:32,979
- Sohrab...
- You can only impress

785
00:39:33,062 --> 00:39:34,437
the chicks in class.

786
00:39:34,521 --> 00:39:37,062
You're absolutely right, Mr Handa.
Philosophy is useless.

787
00:39:37,146 --> 00:39:38,062
Just like art.

788
00:39:38,146 --> 00:39:41,646
There he goes
twisting my words again...

789
00:39:41,937 --> 00:39:43,687
But I'm agreeing with you.

790
00:39:43,687 --> 00:39:45,437
I admit I'm useless.

791
00:39:45,521 --> 00:39:48,021
- Look at him.
- I'm glad I opted out when I did.

792
00:39:48,062 --> 00:39:50,312
- Opted out?
- When were you even in?

793
00:39:50,437 --> 00:39:52,896
You travel around the world
delivering lectures.

794
00:39:52,937 --> 00:39:54,646
You get a fat cheque
from the university.

795
00:39:54,687 --> 00:39:55,646
And you think you opted out?

796
00:39:55,687 --> 00:39:57,937
Please show us how to opt out too.

797
00:39:58,646 --> 00:40:00,937
You get money for nothing...
for just blabbering!

798
00:40:01,062 --> 00:40:04,812
We work our asses off
to earn our daily bread.

799
00:40:05,021 --> 00:40:06,896
You don't add a shit
to the economy.

800
00:40:06,937 --> 00:40:08,646
- True.
- You don't create jobs

801
00:40:08,687 --> 00:40:11,187
You don't generate wealth,
occupation, employment.

802
00:40:11,187 --> 00:40:12,062
Nothing!

803
00:40:12,146 --> 00:40:14,812
- All you do is jabber.
- True, all true...

804
00:40:14,937 --> 00:40:16,396
We move things around.

805
00:40:16,437 --> 00:40:20,687
We're making the world go around.
Get it, Mr Philosopher?

806
00:40:20,771 --> 00:40:22,396
I wouldn't go that far, Handa.

807
00:40:22,896 --> 00:40:24,271
We do real work.

808
00:40:24,437 --> 00:40:25,937
Work!
Ever heard of it?

809
00:40:25,937 --> 00:40:27,062
Labour!

810
00:40:27,187 --> 00:40:29,187
Have you heard of it?
Toil, action...

811
00:40:29,271 --> 00:40:31,062
We sweat it out.

812
00:40:31,187 --> 00:40:33,021
We build.
We create.

813
00:40:33,187 --> 00:40:34,437
We make empires.

814
00:40:34,437 --> 00:40:35,771
Empires also fall, you know.

815
00:40:35,812 --> 00:40:37,187
We'll figure it out
when that happens.

816
00:40:37,562 --> 00:40:38,937
The night is still young.

817
00:40:38,937 --> 00:40:40,396
There is still some life left in us.

818
00:40:40,437 --> 00:40:42,062
Let's say cheers to that.

819
00:40:42,062 --> 00:40:43,437
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

820
00:40:44,062 --> 00:40:46,771
Mr Handa, our ideas
remain beyond us.

821
00:40:46,812 --> 00:40:47,896
You know that, right?

822
00:40:48,187 --> 00:40:50,437
You...
You remain in people's memories.

823
00:40:50,562 --> 00:40:52,896
Who gives a crap about
what people think?

824
00:40:53,062 --> 00:40:54,937
- Really?
- People are shit anyway.

825
00:40:55,521 --> 00:40:56,521
Look at you guys.

826
00:40:56,687 --> 00:40:57,521
- Hey!
- Excuse me.

827
00:40:57,562 --> 00:40:58,312
Please.

828
00:40:58,437 --> 00:41:01,062
Handa, your shit stinks
but we love you, bro.

829
00:41:01,812 --> 00:41:03,937
- Okay. Now stop it.
- All hail Lord Handa!

830
00:41:04,521 --> 00:41:06,187
It's an interesting bunch.

831
00:41:06,312 --> 00:41:08,437
But then I find
most people interesting. So...

832
00:41:08,437 --> 00:41:10,146
Yeah, we know you do.

833
00:41:10,437 --> 00:41:12,062
Come on now.
Tell us.

834
00:41:12,146 --> 00:41:13,521
What?
Tell you what?

835
00:41:13,771 --> 00:41:15,396
- Come on.
- Sing for your supper.

836
00:41:15,437 --> 00:41:17,646
- Chandra, don't be such a bore.
- No, no, no.

837
00:41:18,396 --> 00:41:20,062
They're all lovely people.
That's it.

838
00:41:20,187 --> 00:41:22,437
I'll make it simple.
What do you think about the bully?

839
00:41:23,937 --> 00:41:26,771
By that, I suppose, you mean
your business partner, right?

840
00:41:27,312 --> 00:41:28,104
Yeah.

841
00:41:28,812 --> 00:41:32,521
I'm not sure he's a bully.
I mean, he pretends to be.

842
00:41:34,146 --> 00:41:35,771
But there's something
soft about him.

843
00:41:35,812 --> 00:41:37,687
Almost vulnerable, I feel.

844
00:41:39,937 --> 00:41:42,521
But there are others in the room
who are hard, really hard.

845
00:41:42,562 --> 00:41:43,687
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

846
00:41:43,687 --> 00:41:44,687
Like who?

847
00:41:45,646 --> 00:41:46,646
Like who?

848
00:41:49,521 --> 00:41:51,271
How's your relationship
with your sister?

849
00:41:52,687 --> 00:41:54,771
- Alright! Caught you out.
- That is...

850
00:41:54,812 --> 00:41:55,812
You're terrible.

851
00:41:55,896 --> 00:41:56,896
Okay...

852
00:41:57,687 --> 00:41:59,771
Can you guess who the other bully
in the room is?

853
00:42:00,312 --> 00:42:01,312
Who?

854
00:42:02,021 --> 00:42:06,021
Did Sohrab ever mention
he got beaten up as a kid?

855
00:42:06,396 --> 00:42:07,312
I mean, real bad?

856
00:42:07,687 --> 00:42:09,687
Doc, we all got beaten up as kids.

857
00:42:09,771 --> 00:42:11,062
- I know..
- It was the norm then.

858
00:42:11,312 --> 00:42:14,562
Yeah but this old man,
he was vicious.

859
00:42:15,771 --> 00:42:18,021
Really.
I see him and I see blood.

860
00:42:18,562 --> 00:42:20,437
- Wow.
- That's intense.

861
00:42:20,521 --> 00:42:22,271
Okay, don't stop.
Keep going.

862
00:42:23,271 --> 00:42:24,771
- Don't.
- No. That's it.

863
00:42:24,812 --> 00:42:25,937
That's it for today.

864
00:42:25,937 --> 00:42:27,271
She's not going
to let you off easily.

865
00:42:27,312 --> 00:42:28,646
Maybe on our way back,
I can tell you more.

866
00:42:28,687 --> 00:42:30,312
No.
Some more.

867
00:42:30,312 --> 00:42:31,312
- Come on.
- Okay. Last one.

868
00:42:31,562 --> 00:42:32,562
This...

869
00:42:32,937 --> 00:42:35,562
Nena... And what's his name?
Kumar...

870
00:42:35,937 --> 00:42:38,187
Is there a problem
in their… relationship?

871
00:42:39,812 --> 00:42:41,646
- Wow!
- How do you know?

872
00:42:41,687 --> 00:42:43,437
I'm not wrong, am I?

873
00:42:43,562 --> 00:42:45,437
- No, you're not wrong.
- No. Bang on.

874
00:42:45,687 --> 00:42:47,771
Last month, she came over and...

875
00:42:48,646 --> 00:42:51,229
She said that she's planning
on calling it off with him.

876
00:42:52,146 --> 00:42:54,562
But Kumar doesn't know yet.

877
00:42:54,812 --> 00:42:57,021
Kumar doesn't know it, dammit.
How do you know?

878
00:42:57,146 --> 00:42:58,562
- How do you do it, Chandra?
- Yeah.

879
00:42:58,646 --> 00:43:01,562
I don't know.
I pick up on things.

880
00:43:02,187 --> 00:43:03,771
Okay.
I remember.

881
00:43:05,187 --> 00:43:06,562
She said...

882
00:43:07,521 --> 00:43:09,062
"I finished recording and came."

883
00:43:09,437 --> 00:43:10,854
And he said,
"We finished recording."

884
00:43:10,937 --> 00:43:13,062
And that kind of
sent me a signal.

885
00:43:13,187 --> 00:43:14,687
Wow!
Okay.

886
00:43:15,312 --> 00:43:17,771
I'm not talking in front of you
from now on.

887
00:43:17,812 --> 00:43:19,187
Not happening.

888
00:43:19,312 --> 00:43:21,104
You'll find out
all my dark secrets.

889
00:43:21,312 --> 00:43:23,604
It's alright.
We all have our dark corners.

890
00:43:23,896 --> 00:43:25,562
As long as we learn
how to live with them.

891
00:43:25,562 --> 00:43:26,771
No...

892
00:43:26,937 --> 00:43:28,396
I'm off.
Bye.

893
00:43:28,437 --> 00:43:30,312
- See.
- Bye.

894
00:43:30,687 --> 00:43:31,937
- I'll be right in.
- Okay.

895
00:43:35,354 --> 00:43:36,562
Oh my God!
It moves! It flies!

896
00:43:36,687 --> 00:43:40,021
- This one's for you, my friend.
- Okay, we fly.

897
00:43:40,812 --> 00:43:41,812
Thank you.

898
00:43:41,812 --> 00:43:43,312
- Shall we go in?
- Yeah.

899
00:43:47,396 --> 00:43:48,687
Your cigarettes?

900
00:43:49,437 --> 00:43:51,187
- I don't smoke, Doc.
- Right.

901
00:43:54,562 --> 00:43:55,771
- Listen.
- Hmm.

902
00:43:56,312 --> 00:43:58,437
You and Nena...

903
00:44:02,812 --> 00:44:03,812
Doc...

904
00:44:05,146 --> 00:44:06,937
- Okay, I thought so.
- Yeah.

905
00:44:07,562 --> 00:44:09,562
Something...
Way back.

906
00:44:10,521 --> 00:44:11,646
But there's nothing right now.

907
00:44:11,687 --> 00:44:12,687
- Alright.
- Okay.

908
00:44:13,146 --> 00:44:16,271
And Kumar and Nena
are not splitting because...

909
00:44:17,146 --> 00:44:18,937
No, man.
Are you nuts?

910
00:44:18,937 --> 00:44:20,562
Just checking.

911
00:44:20,937 --> 00:44:23,312
Man, shouldn't have invited you.

912
00:44:23,437 --> 00:44:24,687
There's nothing now.

913
00:44:24,771 --> 00:44:26,021
I believed you the first time.

914
00:44:26,062 --> 00:44:27,437
Why are you repeating yourself?

915
00:44:31,021 --> 00:44:32,937
Kumar, keep it to yourself now.

916
00:44:33,021 --> 00:44:34,937
They are all a pack of wolves!

917
00:44:35,687 --> 00:44:37,146
Don't tell anybody.
Okay?

918
00:44:37,562 --> 00:44:39,312
This is going to be fun.

919
00:44:39,562 --> 00:44:41,396
This is going to be epic shit!

920
00:44:43,187 --> 00:44:46,146
Handa is never going to
sell the company.

921
00:44:50,104 --> 00:44:51,146
What do you want, Arun?

922
00:44:51,437 --> 00:44:53,187
Baba wants water.

923
00:44:53,187 --> 00:44:55,062
The glasses are behind you.

924
00:44:55,437 --> 00:44:57,521
And there's water in the fridge.

925
00:44:58,062 --> 00:45:00,687
Sandeep, this is taking forever.

926
00:45:00,812 --> 00:45:02,521
- Ready in 40 minutes.
- Really?

927
00:45:03,271 --> 00:45:04,937
- Suman, is something burning?
- No. It's fine.

928
00:45:05,021 --> 00:45:06,146
- Are you sure?
- Yes.

929
00:45:06,187 --> 00:45:07,187
Raman.

930
00:45:07,562 --> 00:45:08,937
- Raman?
- Yeah?

931
00:45:10,062 --> 00:45:12,146
What is the thing with Maddy?

932
00:45:12,187 --> 00:45:13,812
- I know..
- Isn't it?

933
00:45:13,937 --> 00:45:17,021
She is no more than 24.
Maybe, 25 at the most.

934
00:45:17,187 --> 00:45:18,187
Yeah...

935
00:45:18,896 --> 00:45:19,687
She is 28.

936
00:45:19,771 --> 00:45:20,812
- Really.
- Yeah, he told me.

937
00:45:20,896 --> 00:45:22,771
She's 28 and he is 52!

938
00:45:23,437 --> 00:45:25,146
He's double her age.

939
00:45:25,437 --> 00:45:26,437
What's going on?

940
00:45:26,562 --> 00:45:28,687
- Is the mutton washed?
- Almost done.

941
00:45:28,771 --> 00:45:31,687
- Men go a little crazy as they age.
- Correct.

942
00:45:31,812 --> 00:45:32,812
It's okay, guys.

943
00:45:32,896 --> 00:45:34,812
- You'll justify it.
- Raman!

944
00:45:35,187 --> 00:45:36,312
Raman!

945
00:45:36,562 --> 00:45:37,812
Have you tried talking to her?

946
00:45:37,937 --> 00:45:39,062
- Raman!
- Yeah.

947
00:45:39,187 --> 00:45:41,479
What do they even talk about?

948
00:45:41,562 --> 00:45:43,187
They wouldn't waste
their time talking.

949
00:45:44,271 --> 00:45:45,146
All day?

950
00:45:47,812 --> 00:45:48,896
Got you, my friend.

951
00:45:49,021 --> 00:45:50,021
Got you.

952
00:45:50,146 --> 00:45:51,312
What is it?
Want something?

953
00:45:52,437 --> 00:45:53,646
I know what you want.

954
00:45:53,687 --> 00:45:55,521
Ma'am, Baba's calling you.

955
00:45:55,687 --> 00:45:56,937
I'll be right there.

956
00:45:57,021 --> 00:45:58,562
Got you, my friend.

957
00:45:58,771 --> 00:46:00,271
Kumar, take it easy.

958
00:46:00,562 --> 00:46:01,562
What's wrong with him?

959
00:46:01,812 --> 00:46:02,812
He's drunk.

960
00:46:02,896 --> 00:46:06,021
- What's his thing?
- Drunk and how!

961
00:46:07,687 --> 00:46:11,312
Does this nurse stay
with them 24x7?

962
00:46:11,396 --> 00:46:13,812
Yeah, they've a 4 bedroom house.
They've given her one.

963
00:46:14,271 --> 00:46:16,937
She takes care of the family.
Come on.

964
00:46:18,354 --> 00:46:19,229
She does.

965
00:46:19,812 --> 00:46:22,396
- What did I say?
- You always twist my words.

966
00:46:22,521 --> 00:46:25,021
I believe you.
She does take care of everybody.

967
00:46:25,187 --> 00:46:26,562
Baba and Arun...

968
00:46:26,646 --> 00:46:27,687
And Sohrab.

969
00:46:29,146 --> 00:46:30,312
She does.

970
00:46:30,646 --> 00:46:32,479
- Jayanti.
- What did I say?

971
00:46:32,562 --> 00:46:34,312
What's going on?
What did I miss?

972
00:46:34,437 --> 00:46:35,937
- Nothing.
- All okay?

973
00:46:36,146 --> 00:46:37,271
Where's my gin?

974
00:46:37,646 --> 00:46:38,562
Is it done?

975
00:46:38,562 --> 00:46:40,312
- Almost done.
- Raman. Here.

976
00:46:40,937 --> 00:46:42,604
Sandy!

977
00:46:42,771 --> 00:46:44,771
- The sambar tastes amazing.
- Thanks.

978
00:46:44,812 --> 00:46:47,021
Sandeep, I'm eating
your mutton curry after ages.

979
00:46:47,271 --> 00:46:48,271
Need anything else?

980
00:46:48,312 --> 00:46:49,937
All the kids, sit there.

981
00:46:50,062 --> 00:46:53,187
Nazia, sit there.
Make space for Nazia.

982
00:46:53,396 --> 00:46:54,937
- Sandeep, this is fabulous.
- Thank you.

983
00:46:55,021 --> 00:46:57,312
What can I get for you, Mr Handa?
At your service.

984
00:46:57,396 --> 00:46:58,812
You are a fake.

985
00:46:58,896 --> 00:47:01,062
You don't have any principles
or beliefs.

986
00:47:01,187 --> 00:47:03,062
But I believe in friendship...

987
00:47:03,437 --> 00:47:04,437
Get lost.

988
00:47:04,562 --> 00:47:06,437
You tell me your name first.

989
00:47:06,437 --> 00:47:07,312
Kumar.

990
00:47:08,187 --> 00:47:09,521
Your real name.

991
00:47:09,687 --> 00:47:12,146
What kind of a name is Kumar?
It's a middle name.

992
00:47:12,187 --> 00:47:14,646
- What's your real name?
- What's in a name, Rose?

993
00:47:14,896 --> 00:47:16,687
I am me and you are you.
That's it.

994
00:47:16,771 --> 00:47:18,812
No.
We are who we are.

995
00:47:19,062 --> 00:47:20,062
And you...

996
00:47:20,771 --> 00:47:22,271
- You are fake.
- Never.

997
00:47:22,312 --> 00:47:23,271
Your life is fake.

998
00:47:23,312 --> 00:47:25,771
My name is Kumar.
Does anyone have a problem with it?

999
00:47:25,812 --> 00:47:28,396
We don't have a problem.
Kumar is a great name, bro.

1000
00:47:28,437 --> 00:47:31,021
You know, it's just a label.
Your name.

1001
00:47:31,312 --> 00:47:34,187
My name is Chandra.
I'm from India.

1002
00:47:34,562 --> 00:47:36,771
What are these?
Just labels I was given.

1003
00:47:37,021 --> 00:47:38,896
- And I became that.
- Correct, Doc.

1004
00:47:39,021 --> 00:47:40,562
He became Kumar.
I became Chandra.

1005
00:47:40,729 --> 00:47:41,646
I became Raman.

1006
00:47:41,771 --> 00:47:44,062
Are you saying we just become
what we're given?

1007
00:47:44,146 --> 00:47:45,562
Well, that's the starting point.

1008
00:47:45,646 --> 00:47:46,937
And we also make ourselves.

1009
00:47:47,021 --> 00:47:49,062
We're constantly
making ourselves, right?

1010
00:47:49,396 --> 00:47:50,604
We pick labels.

1011
00:47:50,687 --> 00:47:54,271
What is hard-working or liberal
or honest?

1012
00:47:54,396 --> 00:47:55,396
These are labels.

1013
00:47:55,437 --> 00:47:57,521
We take them.
Put them on our foreheads.

1014
00:47:57,562 --> 00:47:59,312
And that defines us.
Then we become that.

1015
00:47:59,437 --> 00:48:00,437
I agree with you.

1016
00:48:00,437 --> 00:48:05,562
I think my husband is honest,
diligent and gentlemanly.

1017
00:48:05,562 --> 00:48:07,146
- Shrewd!
- And a great sambhar maker.

1018
00:48:07,187 --> 00:48:08,312
- Yes!
- That's true.

1019
00:48:08,437 --> 00:48:10,187
- New label for you.
- Think he's a gentleman?

1020
00:48:10,687 --> 00:48:11,812
Bollocks!

1021
00:48:12,021 --> 00:48:14,562
Your gentleman can't even
run a business.

1022
00:48:14,687 --> 00:48:17,896
The company is still afloat
because of me.

1023
00:48:18,062 --> 00:48:20,562
If it were up to him,
the business would have tanked.

1024
00:48:20,646 --> 00:48:22,104
Really? You think..

1025
00:48:22,187 --> 00:48:24,021
Raman can't manage
the business on his own?

1026
00:48:24,104 --> 00:48:26,521
But I think you guys
make a good team.

1027
00:48:26,646 --> 00:48:30,187
You know... You play the good cop.
You play the bad cop.

1028
00:48:31,562 --> 00:48:33,021
I don't play.

1029
00:48:33,104 --> 00:48:34,646
I am the bad cop.

1030
00:48:35,312 --> 00:48:37,312
Basically, the thing is...

1031
00:48:37,687 --> 00:48:40,229
You need an ass of steel
to run a business.

1032
00:48:40,312 --> 00:48:41,312
Pardon my French.

1033
00:48:41,437 --> 00:48:42,812
There are kids here, Sohrab.

1034
00:48:43,146 --> 00:48:45,187
If you have steel,
get into business.

1035
00:48:45,562 --> 00:48:47,187
Otherwise, do something else.

1036
00:48:47,312 --> 00:48:49,062
You don't have to run a business.

1037
00:48:49,146 --> 00:48:52,187
No one's forcing you.

1038
00:48:52,312 --> 00:48:53,687
Work in fashion or art.

1039
00:48:53,812 --> 00:48:55,896
Stay at home.
No need to do anything.

1040
00:48:56,021 --> 00:48:57,396
You know what I'm saying?

1041
00:49:02,687 --> 00:49:03,771
What?

1042
00:49:04,437 --> 00:49:05,562
No reaction?

1043
00:49:05,687 --> 00:49:08,437
No protest? Come on,
you guys are becoming boring now.

1044
00:49:08,521 --> 00:49:10,937
No, actually, I think
you're becoming boring.

1045
00:49:11,021 --> 00:49:12,271
And very predictable.

1046
00:49:12,437 --> 00:49:13,562
I like that.

1047
00:49:14,437 --> 00:49:16,896
I like a bit of a challenge.
Want me to up the ante?

1048
00:49:17,062 --> 00:49:19,021
No.
Please spare us the misery.

1049
00:49:19,062 --> 00:49:20,062
Thank you.

1050
00:49:20,187 --> 00:49:24,437
Hard-working, loyal, honest...
These are all good labels.

1051
00:49:24,521 --> 00:49:25,396
- Right, Doc?
- Sure.

1052
00:49:25,437 --> 00:49:29,604
What about mean, rude,
lazy, awful?

1053
00:49:29,687 --> 00:49:30,771
Who'd choose labels like these?

1054
00:49:30,812 --> 00:49:31,937
Hi, I'm Kumar.

1055
00:49:32,687 --> 00:49:33,687
Nazia.

1056
00:49:35,812 --> 00:49:37,396
It's none of my business but...

1057
00:49:37,437 --> 00:49:40,146
Do you know Madhvan
has a wife?

1058
00:49:40,187 --> 00:49:42,437
- He's happily--
- Yeah, I know.

1059
00:49:42,896 --> 00:49:45,396
Maybe, he's not so happy anymore.

1060
00:49:46,521 --> 00:49:49,521
Good.
No secrets. No lies.

1061
00:49:50,062 --> 00:49:51,062
Good one.

1062
00:49:51,396 --> 00:49:53,062
...our own moral
code of conduct.

1063
00:49:53,437 --> 00:49:55,521
We have to form our own morality.

1064
00:49:55,771 --> 00:49:57,062
I think that's the problem.

1065
00:49:57,187 --> 00:50:00,521
When we try and impose our truths
and our beliefs

1066
00:50:00,687 --> 00:50:03,146
on to others.
That's the root of all evil.

1067
00:50:03,229 --> 00:50:05,021
That's the beginning
of evil for sure.

1068
00:50:05,146 --> 00:50:07,437
I don't think people are evil.

1069
00:50:07,562 --> 00:50:09,562
I think they're inherently
good at heart.

1070
00:50:09,771 --> 00:50:11,396
- She is so sweet.
- I'm serious.

1071
00:50:11,437 --> 00:50:13,562
Just trying to
come to terms with--

1072
00:50:13,646 --> 00:50:15,187
Oh my God!

1073
00:50:15,312 --> 00:50:17,812
There goes Ms Twinkle Eyes!

1074
00:50:18,146 --> 00:50:19,687
You're so sweet.

1075
00:50:20,437 --> 00:50:22,062
Everyone is so good.

1076
00:50:22,437 --> 00:50:25,271
This world is so beautiful!
Come on, Jayanti.

1077
00:50:25,937 --> 00:50:27,937
My cake is the best cake.

1078
00:50:28,062 --> 00:50:29,646
I live in a fairytale house.

1079
00:50:29,771 --> 00:50:31,062
My husband is the most handsome...

1080
00:50:31,187 --> 00:50:32,437
You're giving me diabetes.

1081
00:50:32,521 --> 00:50:33,812
Please give me a break.

1082
00:50:38,312 --> 00:50:40,812
You don't have to be so
fricking mean all the time, Sohrab.

1083
00:50:40,896 --> 00:50:41,979
You know that?

1084
00:50:42,187 --> 00:50:43,937
Grow the hell up.

1085
00:50:44,896 --> 00:50:46,271
Why are you getting so touchy?

1086
00:50:46,562 --> 00:50:48,312
- I'm not being touchy, actually.
- Yes, you are.

1087
00:50:48,396 --> 00:50:50,062
Just trying to have
an adult conversation.

1088
00:50:50,187 --> 00:50:52,562
And if you can't have that
then you should...

1089
00:50:52,729 --> 00:50:54,229
I don't know...
Just sit down.

1090
00:50:54,437 --> 00:50:55,646
And try and be social.

1091
00:50:55,812 --> 00:50:57,187
I am being social.

1092
00:50:57,312 --> 00:50:59,312
Why do you think I've come
to your fairytale anniversary?

1093
00:50:59,437 --> 00:51:01,104
I wish you weren't here.

1094
00:51:02,062 --> 00:51:03,396
If wishes were horses.

1095
00:51:03,437 --> 00:51:05,146
- He needs to stop doing this.
- Calm down.

1096
00:51:05,312 --> 00:51:06,146
Bravo!

1097
00:51:06,437 --> 00:51:08,396
I'm glad somebody is finally
giving it to the Handa.

1098
00:51:08,562 --> 00:51:10,021
Shut up and finish your food.

1099
00:51:10,062 --> 00:51:11,562
Everyone has cooked
with so much love.

1100
00:51:11,687 --> 00:51:13,396
- Give him some 'sambhar'.
- Satya, coffee.

1101
00:51:13,896 --> 00:51:16,187
But I'm glad I came.

1102
00:51:17,437 --> 00:51:18,812
Especially,
for your 'sambhar', Raman.

1103
00:51:19,187 --> 00:51:20,896
- It's good, right?
- Very good.

1104
00:51:20,937 --> 00:51:22,312
- It's amazing.
- Have some more.

1105
00:51:23,521 --> 00:51:25,521
Sandeep, give me a cigarette.

1106
00:51:26,896 --> 00:51:27,896
Alright.

1107
00:51:28,312 --> 00:51:30,937
Here's a mealtime game.

1108
00:51:31,562 --> 00:51:32,812
- Shall we try?
- Yeah.

1109
00:51:33,312 --> 00:51:34,146
Go for it, Doc.

1110
00:51:34,562 --> 00:51:36,896
Okay, if you
could be somebody else...

1111
00:51:37,187 --> 00:51:38,396
Anybody else...

1112
00:51:38,646 --> 00:51:39,646
Who would you be?

1113
00:51:39,812 --> 00:51:41,146
I'd be like papa.

1114
00:51:41,604 --> 00:51:42,937
- What?
- Okay.

1115
00:51:43,062 --> 00:51:44,812
- Fine. Okay. Spiderman.
- Spiderman.

1116
00:51:44,896 --> 00:51:46,187
I pick JK Rowling.

1117
00:51:46,312 --> 00:51:47,187
JK Rowling.

1118
00:51:47,687 --> 00:51:48,687
Jhunjhunwala.

1119
00:51:49,896 --> 00:51:50,854
Okay.
Good choice.

1120
00:51:51,062 --> 00:51:52,437
I'd be my mother.

1121
00:51:52,854 --> 00:51:54,646
She was such a lovely lady.
Wasn't she?

1122
00:51:54,771 --> 00:51:57,479
I'll be Sohrab Handa.
Bro, I want to be you.

1123
00:51:57,562 --> 00:52:01,271
- It's beyond you.
- I can always aspire to be...

1124
00:52:03,396 --> 00:52:05,062
Missed your chance this time.

1125
00:52:05,812 --> 00:52:06,812
Next birth.

1126
00:52:06,896 --> 00:52:08,271
Be a proper Kumar first.

1127
00:52:10,312 --> 00:52:11,562
Jayanti, what about you?

1128
00:52:13,146 --> 00:52:14,771
I would be Raman.

1129
00:52:15,021 --> 00:52:16,896
- Always kind.
- So sweet.

1130
00:52:17,771 --> 00:52:18,771
Of course.

1131
00:52:19,146 --> 00:52:21,312
- Don't you have anything to say?
- What did I say?

1132
00:52:21,646 --> 00:52:22,646
Did I say anything?

1133
00:52:22,896 --> 00:52:25,187
Even when I'm quiet
you want to provoke me.

1134
00:52:25,562 --> 00:52:29,146
- Baba, some more mutton?
- Two small pieces and gravy.

1135
00:52:29,521 --> 00:52:32,562
"Two small pieces
and a little gravy."

1136
00:52:32,812 --> 00:52:34,687
Polished off half a kilo already.

1137
00:52:34,812 --> 00:52:36,562
It's okay to indulge
once in a while.

1138
00:52:36,646 --> 00:52:37,771
It's not okay.

1139
00:52:38,021 --> 00:52:40,646
Doctors have forbidden it.
He is surviving on half a kidney.

1140
00:52:40,812 --> 00:52:43,812
That's why this nurse
follows him like a shadow.

1141
00:52:44,646 --> 00:52:45,937
Be good and eat sambar now.

1142
00:52:46,896 --> 00:52:47,896
- Whatever!
- Oh!

1143
00:52:48,187 --> 00:52:50,562
And now he'll play the victim card.

1144
00:52:50,562 --> 00:52:54,021
- Please don't mind him.
- Daddy-o had a surgery recently.

1145
00:52:54,437 --> 00:52:56,021
He gets hormone injections everyday.

1146
00:52:57,396 --> 00:52:59,312
It's all been cleaned
out down there.

1147
00:52:59,396 --> 00:53:00,396
Nothing's left.

1148
00:53:00,687 --> 00:53:01,771
Factory is permanently shut.

1149
00:53:02,437 --> 00:53:04,646
Unfortunately...

1150
00:53:05,146 --> 00:53:08,021
- Can't have siblings anymore.
- You fool!

1151
00:53:08,312 --> 00:53:10,021
I am going to kill you.

1152
00:53:10,937 --> 00:53:11,937
Baba!

1153
00:53:12,062 --> 00:53:14,437
- Will you talk to me like that?
- Baba! Stop it!

1154
00:53:15,687 --> 00:53:17,521
Old man's gone crazy!

1155
00:53:17,646 --> 00:53:20,687
I am going to kill him!

1156
00:53:22,271 --> 00:53:24,521
Stop hitting me like a little girl!

1157
00:53:25,062 --> 00:53:26,562
Signs of life!

1158
00:53:26,687 --> 00:53:28,062
Gabbar Singh!

1159
00:53:29,521 --> 00:53:31,187
Calm down, Baba.

1160
00:53:31,521 --> 00:53:33,979
- The hormone injections are working!
- Enough!

1161
00:53:34,062 --> 00:53:35,312
- Enough!
- Sohrab...

1162
00:53:35,437 --> 00:53:37,812
Otherwise, my father will
become my mother.

1163
00:53:38,187 --> 00:53:39,187
Shut up!

1164
00:53:40,521 --> 00:53:41,271
Mummy!

1165
00:53:41,562 --> 00:53:43,646
Mr Handa is going to be Mrs. Handa.

1166
00:53:43,937 --> 00:53:46,812
- Stop it!
- Daddy-o will be turning into my mommy!

1167
00:53:46,937 --> 00:53:47,937
Stop it.
That's enough.

1168
00:53:48,146 --> 00:53:50,146
Wow!
The old man still has some life in him.

1169
00:53:50,229 --> 00:53:51,229
Sohrab.

1170
00:53:51,687 --> 00:53:54,062
- That's the limit. Just stop.
- It's okay.

1171
00:53:54,812 --> 00:53:57,312
Everyone is entertained.
Not a big deal.

1172
00:53:59,437 --> 00:54:00,937
What's for dessert?

1173
00:54:01,937 --> 00:54:04,521
Where is Ram Gopal Satya?

1174
00:54:11,521 --> 00:54:13,646
Did you guys fight often?

1175
00:54:14,437 --> 00:54:16,146
We didn't fight.

1176
00:54:17,187 --> 00:54:18,896
But there were moments of discord.

1177
00:54:23,187 --> 00:54:24,771
He was my flesh.

1178
00:54:27,687 --> 00:54:29,812
He was a piece of my heart.

1179
00:54:31,896 --> 00:54:33,021
Look at him now.

1180
00:54:38,271 --> 00:54:39,646
Uncle is right.

1181
00:54:41,896 --> 00:54:43,687
Sohrab was a nice man.

1182
00:54:45,562 --> 00:54:47,562
He didn't mean any harm.

1183
00:54:49,812 --> 00:54:51,187
He was a gem.

1184
00:54:52,312 --> 00:54:53,312
It's true.

1185
00:54:54,521 --> 00:54:55,771
He was a remarkable man.

1186
00:54:57,062 --> 00:54:58,687
We misunderstood him.

1187
00:54:59,562 --> 00:55:01,354
He had a good heart and I was...

1188
00:55:01,437 --> 00:55:02,646
Oh please, guys.

1189
00:55:03,021 --> 00:55:04,687
He was a horrible man.

1190
00:55:05,312 --> 00:55:07,187
He was mean and vicious.

1191
00:55:07,312 --> 00:55:08,312
Nena.

1192
00:55:08,937 --> 00:55:10,396
He was not nice.
No!

1193
00:55:10,437 --> 00:55:12,687
- Nena, please.
- I am sorry but it's the truth.

1194
00:55:12,771 --> 00:55:14,521
- Nena, come on.
- Don't speak ill of the dead.

1195
00:55:14,562 --> 00:55:15,521
I wouldn't.

1196
00:55:15,562 --> 00:55:18,687
But you guys are going on and on
about him being a gem.

1197
00:55:19,687 --> 00:55:22,312
You guys couldn't stand his guts
and now he's become a gem?

1198
00:55:22,521 --> 00:55:24,187
Stop it, Nena.

1199
00:55:24,396 --> 00:55:27,562
- Isha, I'm sorry.
- He's my husband. Just stop.

1200
00:55:27,646 --> 00:55:28,396
But this is the truth.

1201
00:55:28,479 --> 00:55:31,312
- Everyone now suddenly...
- How dare you! Just stop!

1202
00:55:31,396 --> 00:55:34,146
Who are you to talk
about my son?

1203
00:55:34,187 --> 00:55:35,396
So you want to defend him now?

1204
00:55:35,479 --> 00:55:36,562
- Yes!
- Nena...

1205
00:55:36,562 --> 00:55:37,812
Two hours ago,
you wanted to kill him.

1206
00:55:37,937 --> 00:55:39,687
- That's our family matter.
- He's my son!

1207
00:55:39,771 --> 00:55:41,812
He was my flesh, my blood!

1208
00:55:42,146 --> 00:55:44,646
Please. Enough of this.

1209
00:55:44,896 --> 00:55:45,896
Please...

1210
00:55:46,146 --> 00:55:47,187
Please, guys.

1211
00:55:48,312 --> 00:55:50,062
We've just lost our friend.

1212
00:55:50,562 --> 00:55:51,896
We're all here...

1213
00:55:53,021 --> 00:55:54,312
thanks to Sohrab.

1214
00:55:55,562 --> 00:55:57,062
And now he's gone.

1215
00:55:58,771 --> 00:56:00,396
May his soul rest in peace.

1216
00:56:01,604 --> 00:56:03,354
If he was this kind of a man...

1217
00:56:03,437 --> 00:56:06,021
I mean,
someone who picked fights...

1218
00:56:06,312 --> 00:56:07,146
Then...

1219
00:56:08,937 --> 00:56:12,562
Then everyone in this room
must have a motive to kill him.

1220
00:56:12,646 --> 00:56:14,062
What are you saying?

1221
00:56:14,062 --> 00:56:16,562
I'm telling you
someone killed him.

1222
00:56:16,812 --> 00:56:19,146
And the killer is one of you.

1223
00:56:19,396 --> 00:56:21,646
Sir, listen.
He was an ass.

1224
00:56:21,687 --> 00:56:24,312
- What are you saying?
- Hear me out.

1225
00:56:24,396 --> 00:56:25,521
- He was a jerk.
- Is this necessary?

1226
00:56:25,604 --> 00:56:27,687
But that's not reason enough
to kill somebody, right?

1227
00:56:27,937 --> 00:56:29,062
- Right, Raman?
- Yeah.

1228
00:56:29,312 --> 00:56:29,896
Maddy?

1229
00:56:30,062 --> 00:56:31,937
Sir, Sohrab was our friend.

1230
00:56:32,021 --> 00:56:33,312
We've been friends for 20 years.

1231
00:56:33,396 --> 00:56:34,396
Sir!

1232
00:56:34,437 --> 00:56:36,062
We'd accepted him
for what he was.

1233
00:56:36,187 --> 00:56:37,396
Sir, think I found it.

1234
00:56:37,437 --> 00:56:38,687
- What?
- The murder weapon.

1235
00:56:42,062 --> 00:56:43,062
It's okay.

1236
00:56:43,062 --> 00:56:44,646
- Put it in the plastic bag.
- Yes, sir.

1237
00:56:46,187 --> 00:56:47,187
Calm her down.

1238
00:56:48,187 --> 00:56:51,312
Call boss and ask him how soon
can he get here.

1239
00:56:56,396 --> 00:56:57,812
I know who did it.

1240
00:57:00,062 --> 00:57:01,062
Who?

1241
00:57:05,062 --> 00:57:05,687
Who?

1242
00:57:07,896 --> 00:57:09,062
He killed himself.

1243
00:57:09,937 --> 00:57:11,187
It was a suicide.

1244
00:57:13,062 --> 00:57:14,062
It was a suicide.

1245
00:57:14,812 --> 00:57:16,521
- Arun.
- I know!

1246
00:57:16,937 --> 00:57:18,312
He hated himself.

1247
00:57:18,396 --> 00:57:19,937
He wanted to end it.
So, he ended it.

1248
00:57:20,646 --> 00:57:22,062
- Suicide?
- Yes.

1249
00:57:22,687 --> 00:57:24,854
So, he slit his own throat...

1250
00:57:26,146 --> 00:57:27,896
hid the knife behind the cupboard...

1251
00:57:29,437 --> 00:57:31,021
and then went back to the sofa?

1252
00:57:33,562 --> 00:57:35,187
Anyone can hide the knife.

1253
00:57:35,771 --> 00:57:38,937
Arun.
Go and rest, sleep.

1254
00:57:39,187 --> 00:57:40,646
You killed him!

1255
00:57:41,646 --> 00:57:42,646
Calm down.

1256
00:57:43,062 --> 00:57:44,687
All of you killed him.

1257
00:57:47,646 --> 00:57:49,562
You killed my brother!
Move!

1258
00:57:50,396 --> 00:57:51,646
- Arun...
- No.

1259
00:57:51,771 --> 00:57:52,771
Let him be.

1260
00:58:19,271 --> 00:58:20,396
I was thinking...

1261
00:58:21,937 --> 00:58:25,062
All this will settle down
in a week or two.

1262
00:58:25,812 --> 00:58:26,812
What about the future?

1263
00:58:28,312 --> 00:58:29,437
What do you mean?

1264
00:58:30,896 --> 00:58:31,896
I mean...

1265
00:58:32,437 --> 00:58:33,771
Life has to go on, right?

1266
00:58:35,062 --> 00:58:36,687
Raman will need a helping hand.

1267
00:58:37,687 --> 00:58:38,687
And Sohrab...

1268
00:58:44,396 --> 00:58:45,687
Talk to Raman...

1269
00:58:46,312 --> 00:58:47,812
...about Sandeep.

1270
00:58:50,937 --> 00:58:54,771
Once he's given responsibility
he can prove himself.

1271
00:58:55,187 --> 00:58:56,146
Right?

1272
00:58:57,312 --> 00:59:00,562
Tell Raman, he's hardworking.
You guys won't be sorry.

1273
00:59:01,812 --> 00:59:02,812
Yeah?

1274
00:59:05,937 --> 00:59:07,646
I'll speak to him later.

1275
00:59:07,896 --> 00:59:09,812
Yeah.
Whenever you get the chance.

1276
00:59:11,021 --> 00:59:13,562
I just wanted you
to keep it in your mind.

1277
00:59:13,687 --> 00:59:14,687
That's it.

1278
00:59:15,062 --> 00:59:16,062
Okay.

1279
00:59:16,771 --> 00:59:18,437
- Wait.
- What?

1280
00:59:19,271 --> 00:59:20,937
Do you know about Isha?

1281
00:59:22,062 --> 00:59:23,062
What?

1282
00:59:24,646 --> 00:59:25,646
She sleepwalks.

1283
00:59:31,062 --> 00:59:32,771
What have you decided,
Mr Qureshi?

1284
00:59:33,562 --> 00:59:34,562
You see...

1285
00:59:35,562 --> 00:59:38,271
That's for my boss to decide.

1286
00:59:40,271 --> 00:59:42,312
We'll just have to wait for him.

1287
00:59:43,437 --> 00:59:45,271
Yeah, but you are boss for now.

1288
00:59:46,896 --> 00:59:48,187
It was an unfortunate accident.

1289
00:59:48,312 --> 00:59:50,146
Will you keep us up all night
for that?

1290
00:59:51,062 --> 00:59:54,146
I'm your fan, Kumar ji.

1291
00:59:54,312 --> 00:59:55,646
I'm not an idiot.

1292
00:59:56,312 --> 00:59:57,312
Huh?

1293
00:59:58,062 --> 01:00:01,896
His throat
did not get slit accidentally.

1294
01:00:02,437 --> 01:00:04,187
This is a murder.

1295
01:00:04,396 --> 01:00:05,396
Premeditated.

1296
01:00:05,687 --> 01:00:07,562
Don't write it off as a mishap.

1297
01:00:07,646 --> 01:00:09,812
Used the wrong word.

1298
01:00:10,312 --> 01:00:11,187
It's a disaster.

1299
01:00:11,312 --> 01:00:12,396
A tragedy.

1300
01:00:12,937 --> 01:00:14,271
He was our friend.

1301
01:00:14,937 --> 01:00:16,896
We're all heartbroken.

1302
01:00:17,812 --> 01:00:19,062
But we have a prime time show.

1303
01:00:19,146 --> 01:00:20,437
Can't skip the recording.

1304
01:00:20,646 --> 01:00:22,187
- So much to do--
- Yes, sir.

1305
01:00:23,021 --> 01:00:24,521
We're right here.

1306
01:00:25,562 --> 01:00:27,521
There's no problem, sir.

1307
01:00:27,937 --> 01:00:29,021
Everything is on track.

1308
01:00:30,646 --> 01:00:31,646
Yes, sir...

1309
01:00:31,687 --> 01:00:33,312
Amar ji, it's up to you now.

1310
01:00:33,646 --> 01:00:35,771
Please find a way.

1311
01:00:37,312 --> 01:00:38,646
How?

1312
01:00:40,021 --> 01:00:41,021
You tell us.

1313
01:00:42,062 --> 01:00:44,187
We're ready...
for whatever needs to be done.

1314
01:00:45,062 --> 01:00:48,104
Are you making an offer?

1315
01:00:51,187 --> 01:00:52,812
We are open to make a deal.

1316
01:00:53,312 --> 01:00:55,146
I'm also open, ma'am.

1317
01:00:56,021 --> 01:00:57,437
He's also generally open.

1318
01:00:58,521 --> 01:00:59,937
But the big boss...

1319
01:01:00,271 --> 01:01:03,812
if he gets a hint of this,
we'd all be in deep shit.

1320
01:01:04,062 --> 01:01:05,312
We have a suspect...

1321
01:01:08,021 --> 01:01:09,437
- Amar ji!
- Yes, sir!

1322
01:01:09,771 --> 01:01:10,812
What happened?

1323
01:01:11,437 --> 01:01:12,437
Sandeep!

1324
01:01:12,771 --> 01:01:14,437
- Arun fell off the tree house.
- Raman.

1325
01:01:14,687 --> 01:01:15,687
Maddy!

1326
01:01:16,021 --> 01:01:16,687
Arun!

1327
01:01:16,771 --> 01:01:17,771
- He's alive.
- Arun!

1328
01:01:17,896 --> 01:01:19,687
- Careful.
- Be careful.

1329
01:01:19,812 --> 01:01:20,562
Isha!

1330
01:01:20,562 --> 01:01:22,312
Wait.
Are you okay?

1331
01:01:26,812 --> 01:01:28,562
Sandeep, come this side.

1332
01:01:28,646 --> 01:01:29,812
What's this?

1333
01:01:29,937 --> 01:01:31,437
- Families should stay together.
- You go there.

1334
01:01:31,437 --> 01:01:33,146
- What are we playing?
- Dumb charades.

1335
01:01:33,937 --> 01:01:35,854
- Come here.
- What's happening?

1336
01:01:36,687 --> 01:01:38,146
Nena, you go there.

1337
01:01:38,187 --> 01:01:39,812
- I'll go there?
- Come, come.

1338
01:01:40,146 --> 01:01:41,312
We'll beat them anyway.

1339
01:01:41,312 --> 01:01:43,896
You guys have just let me go, huh?

1340
01:01:44,312 --> 01:01:46,437
I'm not that bad.

1341
01:01:46,896 --> 01:01:50,271
- We're a better team anyway.
- Okay, start.

1342
01:01:50,771 --> 01:01:52,604
I'm going first.

1343
01:01:54,271 --> 01:01:55,396
I'll give her the name.

1344
01:01:55,479 --> 01:01:58,896
Don't give her an easy one
because she's your sister.

1345
01:01:59,062 --> 01:02:00,271
I can hear you.

1346
01:02:00,354 --> 01:02:01,729
What did you get?

1347
01:02:01,812 --> 01:02:03,687
- Okay.
- We're keeping time.

1348
01:02:03,771 --> 01:02:05,771
Okay, guys. Listen.

1349
01:02:06,062 --> 01:02:08,562
- Hindi.
- One word.

1350
01:02:08,687 --> 01:02:09,937
- It's begun.
- 'Talaq'.

1351
01:02:10,271 --> 01:02:11,187
'Talaq'.

1352
01:02:11,937 --> 01:02:13,937
Why are you only talking to him?
Talk to us too.

1353
01:02:14,021 --> 01:02:16,854
- Wait!
- You're not allowed to talk!

1354
01:02:16,937 --> 01:02:18,979
- Drive...
- You and me, driving.

1355
01:02:20,187 --> 01:02:21,312
- Give up.
- Boy and girl.

1356
01:02:21,312 --> 01:02:22,312
Both of us?

1357
01:02:22,937 --> 01:02:24,812
We were driving?

1358
01:02:25,062 --> 01:02:26,021
You and me driving...

1359
01:02:26,271 --> 01:02:27,271
- And?
- Highway!

1360
01:02:27,312 --> 01:02:28,729
- Bomb blast!
- Bomb! Bomb!

1361
01:02:28,812 --> 01:02:29,979
'Daud?'

1362
01:02:32,062 --> 01:02:34,812
And we got a flat tyre...
We were going for 'Badla'!

1363
01:02:34,937 --> 01:02:35,937
Yes!

1364
01:02:36,021 --> 01:02:37,812
- 'Badla'?
- No, no, no.

1365
01:02:38,062 --> 01:02:40,062
This is cheating.

1366
01:02:40,187 --> 01:02:41,187
How is this cheating?

1367
01:02:41,271 --> 01:02:42,937
You're supposed
to describe the film.

1368
01:02:43,146 --> 01:02:44,271
Not how you saw it.

1369
01:02:44,396 --> 01:02:46,562
I didn't say anything.
It's valid.

1370
01:02:46,562 --> 01:02:48,354
Fair and square, we won.

1371
01:02:48,437 --> 01:02:49,312
We forgive you.

1372
01:02:49,396 --> 01:02:50,396
Thank you.

1373
01:02:50,896 --> 01:02:53,562
Okay, who's next?
Sandeep!

1374
01:02:53,687 --> 01:02:55,146
- Good luck.
- Go get them!

1375
01:02:55,187 --> 01:02:58,271
- Hey, Satya! Get me a drink.
- You're sore losers.

1376
01:02:59,062 --> 01:03:01,687
- Put one cube of ice in this.
- Right away.

1377
01:03:02,312 --> 01:03:03,854
- Kumar, shift a little.
- Okay, ready?

1378
01:03:03,937 --> 01:03:06,646
- Yes, ready.
- Your time starts now.

1379
01:03:06,771 --> 01:03:07,771
English?

1380
01:03:07,937 --> 01:03:08,937
One word.

1381
01:03:09,021 --> 01:03:10,062
- English or Hindi?
- Hindi.

1382
01:03:10,062 --> 01:03:12,479
Tell us clearly.
Hindi or English?

1383
01:03:12,562 --> 01:03:13,562
It's Hindi.

1384
01:03:14,521 --> 01:03:15,437
Dangerous?

1385
01:03:16,687 --> 01:03:17,687
Ghost?

1386
01:03:17,937 --> 01:03:19,146
Anger? Fear?

1387
01:03:19,312 --> 01:03:20,312
Wolf?

1388
01:03:21,187 --> 01:03:22,312
Tiger?

1389
01:03:22,687 --> 01:03:25,396
- Monster? Predator?
- Beast?

1390
01:03:25,437 --> 01:03:27,271
Fear? Fright?

1391
01:03:27,396 --> 01:03:28,396
- Predator?
- Tiger?

1392
01:03:29,062 --> 01:03:31,937
- Do something else.
- Give another hint.

1393
01:03:32,021 --> 01:03:32,937
Bear?

1394
01:03:32,937 --> 01:03:35,271
Please do something else.

1395
01:03:35,771 --> 01:03:37,312
- Bat! Bat!
- Bird?

1396
01:03:37,437 --> 01:03:39,187
- A bat?
- It's a bird!

1397
01:03:39,312 --> 01:03:41,271
- Bird?
- Eagle?

1398
01:03:41,312 --> 01:03:42,771
- Kite!
- Eagle?

1399
01:03:42,937 --> 01:03:45,187
You guys are so bad at this.

1400
01:03:45,271 --> 01:03:47,187
- Witch!
- Pigeon...

1401
01:03:47,312 --> 01:03:48,271
Sohrab Handa!

1402
01:03:48,312 --> 01:03:49,812
Bat!

1403
01:03:50,521 --> 01:03:51,937
Crow!

1404
01:03:52,896 --> 01:03:53,812
- Crow!
- Crow!

1405
01:03:53,896 --> 01:03:54,896
But crow is an English word.

1406
01:03:54,937 --> 01:03:57,396
Okay crow is half the word.

1407
01:03:57,521 --> 01:04:00,562
Crow dancing?
Dancing crow?

1408
01:04:00,812 --> 01:04:03,937
- A dancing crow?
- A crow that dances?

1409
01:04:04,021 --> 01:04:05,687
No. Dancing crow.

1410
01:04:05,771 --> 01:04:06,937
Time is up.

1411
01:04:07,937 --> 01:04:08,937
'Krodh'.

1412
01:04:09,062 --> 01:04:10,646
- 'Krodh'.
- 'Krodh' meaning anger.

1413
01:04:10,812 --> 01:04:12,521
Why were you showing a crow?

1414
01:04:12,937 --> 01:04:13,937
Crow-dha!

1415
01:04:14,812 --> 01:04:15,812
We got the crow part.

1416
01:04:16,687 --> 01:04:19,312
But how would we ever get 'dha'?

1417
01:04:19,437 --> 01:04:20,854
'Ta dhin dhin dha'.

1418
01:04:20,979 --> 01:04:21,979
Crow + dha!

1419
01:04:22,062 --> 01:04:23,396
Come on, Sandeep!

1420
01:04:23,437 --> 01:04:24,896
- Shouldn't have sent you.
- It's okay.

1421
01:04:25,021 --> 01:04:28,021
Did a crow eat your brain?

1422
01:04:28,062 --> 01:04:29,812
You're too cute.

1423
01:04:29,896 --> 01:04:32,437
I'll go.
I'll go.

1424
01:04:32,562 --> 01:04:35,021
Just remember,
you guys are 2-0 behind.

1425
01:04:35,146 --> 01:04:36,771
And we're kicking your butt.

1426
01:04:37,062 --> 01:04:39,312
Who's going to give me the title?

1427
01:04:39,687 --> 01:04:41,437
- I am.
- Oh my God!

1428
01:04:41,562 --> 01:04:42,979
You're going to
give me something?

1429
01:04:44,437 --> 01:04:46,437
Or you'd give me something else?

1430
01:04:46,437 --> 01:04:47,646
I could.

1431
01:04:47,812 --> 01:04:49,062
In front of all these people?

1432
01:04:49,687 --> 01:04:51,229
- We don't mind.
- Okay, come on.

1433
01:04:51,437 --> 01:04:52,562
- May I?
- Go on.

1434
01:04:52,687 --> 01:04:54,771
We can watch this
instead of playing.

1435
01:04:55,812 --> 01:04:57,021
Not tonight.

1436
01:04:57,062 --> 01:04:58,271
Is this 'Gone with the Wind'?

1437
01:04:58,396 --> 01:05:00,521
- What's going on?
- Okay, fine.

1438
01:05:00,937 --> 01:05:02,396
What name did you give him, Isha?

1439
01:05:03,187 --> 01:05:04,146
Three words.

1440
01:05:04,604 --> 01:05:05,854
English.

1441
01:05:06,312 --> 01:05:07,187
Oh sorry.
It's English.

1442
01:05:07,271 --> 01:05:08,312
- First word.
- First word.

1443
01:05:08,437 --> 01:05:09,812
Is it an old film?

1444
01:05:10,521 --> 01:05:14,896
Brother... how nicely you cut it...
I love you, brother... I love you...

1445
01:05:14,937 --> 01:05:16,937
Kumar, let him show properly.

1446
01:05:17,021 --> 01:05:18,021
I love you.

1447
01:05:22,437 --> 01:05:23,437
What's that?

1448
01:05:25,562 --> 01:05:26,687
What are those?

1449
01:05:26,812 --> 01:05:28,812
- Blood oozing out.
- Cutting.

1450
01:05:29,062 --> 01:05:30,937
- Cutting out.
- Cutting.

1451
01:05:32,312 --> 01:05:34,271
This is from when I was 13.

1452
01:05:34,812 --> 01:05:37,271
This, when I was 18.

1453
01:05:37,812 --> 01:05:40,812
This one is pretty recent.

1454
01:05:40,937 --> 01:05:42,062
Want to play something else?

1455
01:05:42,187 --> 01:05:44,021
You guys are really bad at this.

1456
01:05:48,396 --> 01:05:49,937
Arun has fallen down.
Raman, come.

1457
01:05:50,187 --> 01:05:51,812
Be careful.
Easy there.

1458
01:05:52,937 --> 01:05:54,187
What happened, Arun?

1459
01:05:54,646 --> 01:05:55,646
Are you okay?

1460
01:05:55,812 --> 01:05:57,521
What were you doing up there?

1461
01:05:57,646 --> 01:05:59,687
- Any broken bones?
- Oh my God!

1462
01:06:00,021 --> 01:06:01,771
- Take him in.
- Is the leg broken?

1463
01:06:02,146 --> 01:06:04,437
- Careful.
- It's not broken.

1464
01:06:04,646 --> 01:06:06,937
What happened, Arun?

1465
01:06:07,062 --> 01:06:08,687
Please relax.

1466
01:06:09,646 --> 01:06:10,896
But how did he slip like that?

1467
01:06:11,021 --> 01:06:11,896
That's really bad.

1468
01:06:11,937 --> 01:06:14,437
- Careful.
- We should put turmeric. Satya!

1469
01:06:14,521 --> 01:06:15,187
No need.

1470
01:06:15,312 --> 01:06:18,187
I have an ointment.
It works like magic.

1471
01:06:18,312 --> 01:06:19,312
-I'll get it.
-Ice.

1472
01:06:19,812 --> 01:06:21,062
One second.

1473
01:06:21,396 --> 01:06:22,937
What were you doing there?

1474
01:06:23,271 --> 01:06:24,271
Huh?

1475
01:06:25,271 --> 01:06:26,812
Who asked you to go there?

1476
01:06:27,562 --> 01:06:29,396
Is anything broken?

1477
01:06:30,937 --> 01:06:31,937
No, it's fine.

1478
01:06:32,812 --> 01:06:34,812
Oh God!
How did he fall?

1479
01:06:34,896 --> 01:06:36,396
How would he fall like that?

1480
01:06:37,437 --> 01:06:38,771
Did you lose your footing?

1481
01:06:40,521 --> 01:06:41,854
Did someone push you?

1482
01:06:43,312 --> 01:06:44,479
Maybe...

1483
01:06:46,187 --> 01:06:47,812
- I'm just asking.
- Sorry.

1484
01:06:49,562 --> 01:06:51,521
Who was it?
Did you see him?

1485
01:07:00,854 --> 01:07:03,271
- No.
- What the hell is going on?

1486
01:07:03,687 --> 01:07:05,687
Who has gone bonkers?
What's going on?

1487
01:07:05,812 --> 01:07:07,521
Who's doing this to us?

1488
01:07:08,937 --> 01:07:10,896
Do you want to kill us all,
one by one?

1489
01:07:11,021 --> 01:07:12,312
Raman, please stop.

1490
01:07:12,437 --> 01:07:13,437
Who is it?

1491
01:07:13,771 --> 01:07:15,771
- You? You? You?
- Raman!

1492
01:07:18,396 --> 01:07:20,771
- Did you take money from my bag?
- No.

1493
01:07:22,187 --> 01:07:24,937
My money is missing.
My money has been stolen.

1494
01:07:25,562 --> 01:07:27,562
Someone stole 20 thousand bucks
from my bag.

1495
01:07:27,646 --> 01:07:29,062
Who's going to take
your money, Suman?

1496
01:07:29,146 --> 01:07:30,812
There were 10 bills of 2000.

1497
01:07:30,896 --> 01:07:32,146
Must be somewhere.

1498
01:07:32,312 --> 01:07:34,271
I'm telling you
it was stolen.

1499
01:07:34,396 --> 01:07:36,312
Someone stole money
from my bag.

1500
01:07:36,437 --> 01:07:37,646
Who'd steal money?

1501
01:07:37,687 --> 01:07:38,687
How would I know?

1502
01:07:38,687 --> 01:07:41,312
Please check carefully.
It's probably still there.

1503
01:07:41,437 --> 01:07:43,604
- I checked everywhere.
- You'll get it back.

1504
01:07:44,062 --> 01:07:45,646
- Here's the turmeric.
- Ask him.

1505
01:07:45,937 --> 01:07:46,937
Satya.

1506
01:07:47,562 --> 01:07:48,562
Yes, ma'am?

1507
01:07:48,687 --> 01:07:51,062
Did you take the money
from the bag?

1508
01:07:51,896 --> 01:07:53,687
No, I didn't, ma'am.

1509
01:07:53,687 --> 01:07:55,521
Stop lying!
Own up.

1510
01:07:56,187 --> 01:07:58,771
- Sir, I haven't stolen any money.
- Then who did?

1511
01:07:58,812 --> 01:08:00,562
- Did I?
- Tell us the truth, Satya.

1512
01:08:00,687 --> 01:08:02,062
Search him.

1513
01:08:02,562 --> 01:08:03,562
He must have it.

1514
01:08:03,687 --> 01:08:05,937
- He said he didn't do it.
- I don't have anything.

1515
01:08:06,271 --> 01:08:07,521
Get him here.

1516
01:08:08,562 --> 01:08:09,937
- What is this?
- Sir...

1517
01:08:10,062 --> 01:08:12,979
There's been a theft
and you're showing me your pockets?

1518
01:08:13,187 --> 01:08:15,354
- Why are you hitting him?
- What are you doing?

1519
01:08:15,562 --> 01:08:17,728
Please stay out of it.
Let us do our work.

1520
01:08:17,937 --> 01:08:18,937
Take him in.

1521
01:08:19,187 --> 01:08:21,228
He said he hasn't taken it.

1522
01:08:21,312 --> 01:08:23,312
Got the poor man in trouble.

1523
01:08:23,437 --> 01:08:24,687
You didn't steal this?

1524
01:08:25,062 --> 01:08:27,021
No, sir, I swear I haven't.

1525
01:08:27,062 --> 01:08:28,687
It magically appeared here?

1526
01:08:30,437 --> 01:08:33,312
- Sir... That man gave it to me.
- Who?

1527
01:08:34,687 --> 01:08:36,687
Speak up.
What's his name?

1528
01:08:36,896 --> 01:08:38,896
The one, who is slightly fat.

1529
01:08:39,812 --> 01:08:41,562
Mr Qureshi,
he's trying to be smart.

1530
01:08:41,687 --> 01:08:43,687
Lock him up.
These guys are all thieves!

1531
01:08:44,146 --> 01:08:47,103
No, sir, I'm not lying.
He gave it to me.

1532
01:08:47,896 --> 01:08:51,437
He asked me not to tell anyone.

1533
01:08:54,521 --> 01:08:55,687
Not to tell anyone, what?

1534
01:09:05,187 --> 01:09:06,687
- Bring him out.
- Did you find the money?

1535
01:09:06,812 --> 01:09:07,812
Yeah, he had it.

1536
01:09:07,937 --> 01:09:10,062
Show me who it was.

1537
01:09:12,062 --> 01:09:13,062
Hmm?

1538
01:09:13,687 --> 01:09:15,187
Tell us who gave you the money.

1539
01:09:15,687 --> 01:09:18,312
I'm sure it's him.
He's lying. Give him a tight one.

1540
01:09:18,396 --> 01:09:19,396
Come on.

1541
01:09:19,437 --> 01:09:22,187
Are you going to speak up
or should I take you to the station?

1542
01:09:23,187 --> 01:09:24,687
- It was him.
- What?

1543
01:09:24,728 --> 01:09:25,687
He gave me the money.

1544
01:09:25,896 --> 01:09:27,478
What rubbish!

1545
01:09:28,312 --> 01:09:29,687
He stole the money.

1546
01:09:30,062 --> 01:09:31,271
Why would Sandeep
give him money?

1547
01:09:31,687 --> 01:09:32,812
Right, Sandeep?

1548
01:09:32,812 --> 01:09:34,521
Why would I give him money?

1549
01:09:34,562 --> 01:09:37,562
Sir, he gave it to me.
He was washing blood off his hands.

1550
01:09:37,937 --> 01:09:40,687
When I saw him,
he asked me to wait.

1551
01:09:40,812 --> 01:09:44,437
He went in and got the money.
And asked me not to tell anyone.

1552
01:09:45,187 --> 01:09:47,062
- Are you sure you saw it?
- Yes, sir.

1553
01:09:47,896 --> 01:09:49,146
- Sure?
- Yes, sir.

1554
01:09:49,687 --> 01:09:51,396
This is nonsense.

1555
01:09:51,521 --> 01:09:53,271
- I'm telling the truth.
- Who the hell are you?

1556
01:09:53,312 --> 01:09:54,396
I'm the caretaker.

1557
01:09:54,437 --> 01:09:55,521
Did you give him the money?

1558
01:09:57,646 --> 01:10:00,312
- Did you?
- Yes, gave him a little tip.

1559
01:10:00,437 --> 01:10:01,437
Sandeep!

1560
01:10:01,812 --> 01:10:03,312
Rs. 20,000 as a tip?

1561
01:10:04,187 --> 01:10:05,687
It was from all of us.

1562
01:10:05,812 --> 01:10:06,812
Who asked you to?

1563
01:10:07,021 --> 01:10:08,396
What time was this?

1564
01:10:09,021 --> 01:10:10,021
About 12:30.

1565
01:10:10,521 --> 01:10:13,312
What about the blood
you were washing off?

1566
01:10:13,396 --> 01:10:14,396
He's lying.

1567
01:10:14,521 --> 01:10:16,646
Is he lying?
Or are you lying?

1568
01:10:17,771 --> 01:10:19,146
- Huh?
- Sandeep?

1569
01:10:19,312 --> 01:10:20,687
Say something, Sandeep.

1570
01:10:21,146 --> 01:10:22,896
I...

1571
01:10:23,229 --> 01:10:24,187
Yes?

1572
01:10:24,312 --> 01:10:26,771
I had come out for a smoke.

1573
01:10:26,812 --> 01:10:29,271
Sohrab was already dead.

1574
01:10:29,396 --> 01:10:31,646
The knife was on the floor.
I picked it up. Got blood on my hands.

1575
01:10:31,771 --> 01:10:33,521
- I was washing the blood when--
- Okay, that's enough!

1576
01:10:34,021 --> 01:10:35,687
- You can't do this.
- Raman!

1577
01:10:35,937 --> 01:10:37,562
- Baba!
- One minute.

1578
01:10:38,187 --> 01:10:39,854
Wait!

1579
01:10:39,937 --> 01:10:40,937
I haven't done anything.

1580
01:10:42,062 --> 01:10:44,187
Sandeep, look at me.
Did you do it?

1581
01:10:44,312 --> 01:10:47,187
No! Why would I kill him?
He was like my brother.

1582
01:10:47,271 --> 01:10:50,104
- He hasn't done it.
- Take him away.

1583
01:10:50,187 --> 01:10:51,812
- He wouldn't lie to me...
- Move!

1584
01:10:53,937 --> 01:10:56,437
- What are you doing?
- Let me do my job.

1585
01:10:57,062 --> 01:10:57,896
I didn't kill him.

1586
01:10:58,146 --> 01:11:00,646
- Let's go.
- I didn't kill him.

1587
01:11:00,687 --> 01:11:02,562
- Swear on God.
- Are you a leftie?

1588
01:11:02,562 --> 01:11:03,562
I swear I didn't kill him.

1589
01:11:03,687 --> 01:11:05,479
- I...
- Are you a leftie?

1590
01:11:05,562 --> 01:11:06,687
Yes.

1591
01:11:06,771 --> 01:11:08,604
- Suman.
- You use your left hand for everything?

1592
01:11:08,687 --> 01:11:09,687
Yes.

1593
01:11:09,812 --> 01:11:12,437
- Are you a leftie?
- Yes, he is. He's a leftie.

1594
01:11:12,937 --> 01:11:14,187
- Amar ji.
- Yes, sir.

1595
01:11:14,312 --> 01:11:15,562
Let him go.

1596
01:11:15,646 --> 01:11:16,437
Why, sir?

1597
01:11:16,437 --> 01:11:17,896
Why are you letting him go?

1598
01:11:18,021 --> 01:11:20,062
Because, ma'am,
he didn't do it.

1599
01:11:20,312 --> 01:11:21,312
How do you know?

1600
01:11:21,396 --> 01:11:22,396
He's a leftie.

1601
01:11:22,687 --> 01:11:24,437
And the murderer is right-handed.

1602
01:11:24,937 --> 01:11:26,812
The throat has been slit
left to right.

1603
01:11:26,896 --> 01:11:29,146
I told you he hasn't done it.

1604
01:11:29,271 --> 01:11:30,396
Why did you lie?

1605
01:11:30,521 --> 01:11:33,062
I didn't lie, he had blood on
his hand, he gave me money.

1606
01:11:33,187 --> 01:11:34,937
I would make you confess.

1607
01:11:35,021 --> 01:11:38,354
So, you'd blackmail him?

1608
01:11:38,437 --> 01:11:39,937
- He did it.
- I didn't do it, sir.

1609
01:11:40,021 --> 01:11:41,062
- I'm sure he did it.
- Stop it! Raman!

1610
01:11:41,187 --> 01:11:43,271
One slap and he'll confess.

1611
01:11:43,396 --> 01:11:44,771
It's not him, Raman.

1612
01:11:44,937 --> 01:11:46,146
How do you know, Chandra?

1613
01:11:46,187 --> 01:11:48,187
Because it's way too convenient
if it's him.

1614
01:11:48,312 --> 01:11:49,312
Now she can talk.

1615
01:11:49,396 --> 01:11:50,896
Yes.
It's not him.

1616
01:11:51,271 --> 01:11:52,812
It's you.
It's one of you.

1617
01:11:52,937 --> 01:11:54,146
Who the hell are you?

1618
01:11:54,937 --> 01:11:55,979
Take a breath, please.

1619
01:11:56,562 --> 01:11:57,687
Everyone.

1620
01:12:03,271 --> 01:12:04,271
Stop crying!

1621
01:12:04,812 --> 01:12:06,354
- Go inside and cry if you have to.
- Arun.

1622
01:12:06,437 --> 01:12:08,562
- Stop stinking up the room.
- Arun!

1623
01:12:18,937 --> 01:12:20,187
You lied to me?

1624
01:12:21,812 --> 01:12:22,979
How could you?

1625
01:12:26,062 --> 01:12:27,187
Here's the thing, you know...

1626
01:12:28,021 --> 01:12:30,187
- They really stood by us.
- Yeah.

1627
01:12:30,646 --> 01:12:32,062
Both, Raman and Jayanti.

1628
01:12:32,521 --> 01:12:34,437
Who is older of the two of you?

1629
01:12:37,812 --> 01:12:39,146
Take a guess.

1630
01:12:39,437 --> 01:12:40,437
No idea.

1631
01:12:40,562 --> 01:12:42,562
- You can't tell, right?
- No...

1632
01:12:43,937 --> 01:12:47,146
- I'm am older by five years.
- Okay. Really?

1633
01:12:48,062 --> 01:12:50,271
I've taken care of her
more than our mom.

1634
01:12:51,146 --> 01:12:53,271
Your father passed away quite early.

1635
01:12:53,312 --> 01:12:54,437
Yeah.

1636
01:12:55,312 --> 01:12:56,937
Too soon.

1637
01:12:57,771 --> 01:12:58,937
He was so young.

1638
01:12:59,896 --> 01:13:03,021
I was probably 10 years old.

1639
01:13:03,937 --> 01:13:07,062
Papa had a serious drinking problem.

1640
01:13:07,187 --> 01:13:08,187
I see.

1641
01:13:08,187 --> 01:13:10,812
His liver was damaged.

1642
01:13:11,312 --> 01:13:13,521
That's why I don't let him
drink at all.

1643
01:13:13,604 --> 01:13:14,937
No drinking allowed.

1644
01:13:15,187 --> 01:13:16,771
Haven't had a drink in 15 years.

1645
01:13:16,812 --> 01:13:18,646
Oh please now.
Don't make me start.

1646
01:13:18,937 --> 01:13:21,104
When was the last time
I had a drink?

1647
01:13:21,187 --> 01:13:23,562
You dare take one sip.

1648
01:13:25,271 --> 01:13:27,312
You're scolding me
for something I may do in future.

1649
01:13:27,437 --> 01:13:29,437
I have to scold him.

1650
01:13:29,812 --> 01:13:31,896
To keep him in line.

1651
01:13:31,937 --> 01:13:34,229
You don't know him.
He can do anything.

1652
01:13:34,312 --> 01:13:35,521
- Yeah?
- Anything at all.

1653
01:13:38,437 --> 01:13:39,771
Good night!

1654
01:13:39,896 --> 01:13:41,562
Good night, Nazia.

1655
01:13:41,687 --> 01:13:43,437
Bye.

1656
01:13:43,562 --> 01:13:45,687
We'll leave
by 7 tomorrow, Madhvan.

1657
01:13:46,062 --> 01:13:47,729
Yes, I'll be up and about.

1658
01:13:48,312 --> 01:13:49,437
That's a six.
Not a nine.

1659
01:13:49,562 --> 01:13:51,396
I need to leave too.

1660
01:13:52,646 --> 01:13:54,021
Nena, stay a little longer.

1661
01:13:54,062 --> 01:13:56,146
Have to wake up early.
Have to drive.

1662
01:13:56,562 --> 01:13:57,771
Come on.
Your turn.

1663
01:13:58,396 --> 01:13:59,021
Sleep well.

1664
01:13:59,312 --> 01:14:00,312
Satya!

1665
01:14:01,312 --> 01:14:03,312
Put the cake in the fridge.

1666
01:14:03,896 --> 01:14:07,146
Don't take the cake away.
Let it be.

1667
01:14:07,646 --> 01:14:10,521
Keep it back.
For midnight munchies.

1668
01:14:11,771 --> 01:14:13,021
Leaving it for you!

1669
01:14:13,187 --> 01:14:14,187
Thank you.

1670
01:14:14,187 --> 01:14:15,521
- Good night.
- Good night, Doctor .

1671
01:14:15,646 --> 01:14:17,396
- Good night, Doctor.
- Good night, Handa Saheb.

1672
01:14:19,354 --> 01:14:20,354
Let's go.

1673
01:14:20,896 --> 01:14:21,896
I'm done.

1674
01:14:21,937 --> 01:14:23,646
One more game.
Please.

1675
01:14:24,021 --> 01:14:25,021
One more, please.

1676
01:14:26,521 --> 01:14:27,521
Let's go.

1677
01:14:34,979 --> 01:14:36,687
This wasn't such a great idea.

1678
01:14:37,896 --> 01:14:38,896
No?

1679
01:14:39,312 --> 01:14:40,312
Nope.

1680
01:14:43,187 --> 01:14:44,896
I wanted you to meet the gang.

1681
01:14:45,646 --> 01:14:47,521
Yeah, but they're a bit strange.

1682
01:14:48,271 --> 01:14:49,271
Huh?

1683
01:14:50,562 --> 01:14:51,937
Come on.
They're okay.

1684
01:14:52,062 --> 01:14:53,396
Yeah, they're okay.

1685
01:14:53,562 --> 01:14:54,562
They're just...

1686
01:14:56,021 --> 01:14:57,771
I don't know.
They're just...

1687
01:15:00,312 --> 01:15:02,187
- What?
- They're old.

1688
01:15:03,396 --> 01:15:04,771
Something like that.

1689
01:15:04,937 --> 01:15:05,937
That they are.

1690
01:15:06,562 --> 01:15:07,562
Yeah.

1691
01:15:08,437 --> 01:15:09,771
Don't judge them for being old.

1692
01:15:09,854 --> 01:15:11,229
I'm not judging them.

1693
01:15:12,646 --> 01:15:13,937
I don't judge you.

1694
01:15:16,146 --> 01:15:17,146
That's true.

1695
01:15:17,812 --> 01:15:18,812
Yeah.

1696
01:15:18,937 --> 01:15:20,062
But then again...

1697
01:15:21,062 --> 01:15:22,437
You're not old.

1698
01:15:22,687 --> 01:15:23,687
Are you?

1699
01:15:24,687 --> 01:15:27,021
- No, I'm not.
- No, you're not.

1700
01:15:32,396 --> 01:15:33,562
I don't like it, Raman.

1701
01:15:33,562 --> 01:15:35,562
He's not even going to agree.
And...

1702
01:15:36,312 --> 01:15:38,687
He's going to hold it against you
all his life, so...

1703
01:15:38,812 --> 01:15:39,812
What should I do?

1704
01:15:39,979 --> 01:15:41,729
Should I be scared
for the rest of my life?

1705
01:15:41,812 --> 01:15:43,562
Because Handa is going to be mad
at me.

1706
01:15:43,979 --> 01:15:45,687
You don't have to deal
with him everyday.

1707
01:15:45,812 --> 01:15:48,021
- I do.
- I know, babe, but...

1708
01:15:48,562 --> 01:15:50,104
Everything is going well.

1709
01:15:50,187 --> 01:15:51,312
I'm saying why--

1710
01:15:51,396 --> 01:15:53,562
Why are you saying anything at all?

1711
01:15:54,104 --> 01:15:55,896
I'm handling it.

1712
01:15:56,271 --> 01:15:58,687
I need to believe
this is going to work out.

1713
01:15:58,771 --> 01:16:00,896
You just keep filling my head
with doubts.

1714
01:16:01,062 --> 01:16:02,062
Why?

1715
01:16:03,562 --> 01:16:04,771
Okay.
Fine.

1716
01:16:06,937 --> 01:16:08,937
Do whatever you want.

1717
01:16:09,312 --> 01:16:11,437
Do it the way you want,
with whoever you want.

1718
01:16:13,812 --> 01:16:14,812
Hey.

1719
01:16:16,646 --> 01:16:18,312
Look, I...

1720
01:16:18,396 --> 01:16:19,771
Just... Please...

1721
01:16:30,687 --> 01:16:33,187
Have you fallen asleep
in the bathroom?

1722
01:16:36,937 --> 01:16:39,312
Why didn't you die
as soon as you were born?

1723
01:16:40,812 --> 01:16:42,312
You are like a stone
around my neck.

1724
01:16:48,771 --> 01:16:50,312
Guys, is there any left?

1725
01:16:50,437 --> 01:16:51,771
Look at that.

1726
01:16:52,062 --> 01:16:54,937
The philosopher falls
for a mere cake.

1727
01:16:55,562 --> 01:16:59,437
Handa Saheb,
I tried really hard but...

1728
01:16:59,687 --> 01:17:01,437
couldn't resist it.

1729
01:17:01,562 --> 01:17:04,062
Why should you?
To hell with self-control.

1730
01:17:04,437 --> 01:17:06,437
You won't become fat
in a day.

1731
01:17:06,771 --> 01:17:07,771
You know something?

1732
01:17:07,812 --> 01:17:09,521
You're absolutely right.

1733
01:17:09,937 --> 01:17:12,812
Maddy, can you take a photo
of us, please?

1734
01:17:14,521 --> 01:17:15,812
- Okay.
- One more.

1735
01:17:17,062 --> 01:17:18,062
Okay, got it.

1736
01:17:20,812 --> 01:17:21,812
Here you go.

1737
01:17:21,896 --> 01:17:22,771
Thank you.

1738
01:17:23,021 --> 01:17:23,896
Good night, guys.

1739
01:17:23,937 --> 01:17:25,312
Good night, Professor.

1740
01:17:26,562 --> 01:17:27,812
Look at this.

1741
01:17:30,271 --> 01:17:31,687
- So nice.
- Hmm.

1742
01:18:26,187 --> 01:18:27,562
What happened, sir?

1743
01:18:27,771 --> 01:18:29,312
- Did you cut your hand?
- Yes.

1744
01:18:31,437 --> 01:18:33,146
-Don't tell anyone.
-What?

1745
01:18:33,312 --> 01:18:34,646
That you cut your hand?

1746
01:18:35,312 --> 01:18:37,312
Just don't say anything, okay?

1747
01:18:38,062 --> 01:18:39,271
Don't say what?

1748
01:18:39,312 --> 01:18:40,437
I don't get it, sir.

1749
01:18:40,812 --> 01:18:42,271
Wait here.

1750
01:18:59,562 --> 01:19:00,562
Sir...

1751
01:19:02,062 --> 01:19:04,062
Keep it.
It's your tip, from all of us.

1752
01:19:04,437 --> 01:19:05,437
Thank you, sir.

1753
01:19:06,687 --> 01:19:08,562
- You can go.
- Okay, sir.

1754
01:19:24,437 --> 01:19:25,437
Jayanti.

1755
01:19:26,771 --> 01:19:27,687
Sandeep.

1756
01:19:30,187 --> 01:19:31,312
What happened?

1757
01:19:41,312 --> 01:19:43,479
You came, ate some cake
and left.

1758
01:19:44,979 --> 01:19:48,604
And madam, at about 12:15,
you went to sleep.

1759
01:19:49,062 --> 01:19:50,062
Yes.

1760
01:19:51,187 --> 01:19:54,021
When you came down at 12:40

1761
01:19:54,562 --> 01:19:56,646
he was already dead
according to you.

1762
01:19:56,687 --> 01:19:57,812
Yes.

1763
01:19:58,187 --> 01:19:59,187
Got it.

1764
01:19:59,312 --> 01:20:02,896
So between 12:15 and 12:40,

1765
01:20:02,937 --> 01:20:04,437
did anyone see anything?

1766
01:20:05,479 --> 01:20:06,354
Anything at all?

1767
01:20:06,521 --> 01:20:08,479
I had already crashed.

1768
01:20:08,687 --> 01:20:10,187
We were also asleep.

1769
01:20:11,062 --> 01:20:13,312
Around 12:30...

1770
01:20:15,812 --> 01:20:17,562
I heard a loud noise...

1771
01:20:18,187 --> 01:20:20,146
of a door banging shut.
Very loud.

1772
01:20:20,187 --> 01:20:21,562
Actually, that's true.

1773
01:20:21,646 --> 01:20:24,062
I'd heard a loud bang
in the middle of the night.

1774
01:20:24,062 --> 01:20:25,187
There was, right?

1775
01:20:25,521 --> 01:20:28,604
Which door was it?

1776
01:20:28,937 --> 01:20:30,646
I'm not sure.
One of the doors.

1777
01:20:30,687 --> 01:20:32,062
Okay, fine.
No problem.

1778
01:20:32,271 --> 01:20:34,062
- Amar ji, do something.
- Yes, sir.

1779
01:20:34,687 --> 01:20:37,896
- Shut all the doors one by one.
- Okay, sir.

1780
01:20:37,937 --> 01:20:40,937
Try to identify which door it was.

1781
01:20:41,062 --> 01:20:43,146
- But they--
- Let's try.

1782
01:20:43,437 --> 01:20:44,437
You'll figure it out.

1783
01:20:46,354 --> 01:20:48,146
- This one?
- Amazing!

1784
01:20:48,521 --> 01:20:49,521
Amazing!

1785
01:20:50,312 --> 01:20:54,896
When Nena told me first,
I thought it was impossible.

1786
01:20:55,687 --> 01:20:57,021
Sohrab would never agree.

1787
01:20:57,146 --> 01:20:58,187
- Never.
- Kumar, please.

1788
01:20:58,187 --> 01:21:00,187
- At least, your problem is solved.
- Kumar!

1789
01:21:00,312 --> 01:21:01,521
He'd never have agreed.

1790
01:21:01,687 --> 01:21:03,396
You're being very
insensitive, Kumar.

1791
01:21:03,687 --> 01:21:04,896
- Insensitive?
- Yeah.

1792
01:21:05,062 --> 01:21:07,062
I am the insensitive one here?

1793
01:21:07,187 --> 01:21:08,812
What wouldn't he agree to?

1794
01:21:08,937 --> 01:21:10,062
Nothing, I'll tell you later.

1795
01:21:10,146 --> 01:21:11,937
Why don't you tell her now?

1796
01:21:12,062 --> 01:21:13,437
The person you were
hiding it from is dead.

1797
01:21:13,521 --> 01:21:14,771
- Oh my God!
- Kumar!

1798
01:21:15,062 --> 01:21:17,104
- How can you talk like that?
- Did you know?

1799
01:21:17,562 --> 01:21:19,271
He wanted Nena
to invest in the company.

1800
01:21:19,312 --> 01:21:20,771
To buy out Sohrab's share.

1801
01:21:20,896 --> 01:21:23,021
Did you know?
This was going on behind your back.

1802
01:21:23,062 --> 01:21:23,729
Stop it.

1803
01:21:23,812 --> 01:21:25,896
- Now you're ashamed to admit it.
- Can you please...

1804
01:21:25,937 --> 01:21:27,979
- Why can't you tell everyone?
- Please be quiet.

1805
01:21:28,062 --> 01:21:28,937
What is he saying, Raman?

1806
01:21:29,062 --> 01:21:31,937
- It's not what you're thinking.
- It's exactly what she's thinking.

1807
01:21:32,062 --> 01:21:33,062
Jayanti?

1808
01:21:33,771 --> 01:21:34,896
Did you know about this?

1809
01:21:35,687 --> 01:21:36,937
Jayanti knew?

1810
01:21:37,021 --> 01:21:38,187
- You knew about it?
- There's nothing to know.

1811
01:21:38,271 --> 01:21:39,062
Such hypocrites!

1812
01:21:39,812 --> 01:21:42,937
- I was begging you.
- We were just talking.

1813
01:21:43,437 --> 01:21:44,646
What kind of people are you?

1814
01:21:44,687 --> 01:21:47,562
Ready to stab anybody
in the back?

1815
01:21:47,687 --> 01:21:50,271
Today it's Sohrab.
Tomorrow it might be Nena.

1816
01:21:50,312 --> 01:21:51,521
Then somebody else.

1817
01:21:51,937 --> 01:21:53,979
You didn't think of Sandeep
at all?

1818
01:21:54,062 --> 01:21:56,062
Or your sister?

1819
01:21:56,271 --> 01:21:58,187
Do relationships mean
anything to you?

1820
01:21:58,437 --> 01:22:00,396
You only care about money.

1821
01:22:00,437 --> 01:22:02,771
- Selfish people!
- Suman, let it go.

1822
01:22:02,812 --> 01:22:05,187
Kumar, was this necessary?

1823
01:22:05,312 --> 01:22:07,729
- I can't stand his charade!
- Yeah, right!

1824
01:22:07,812 --> 01:22:10,021
You were going to cut Sohrab out?

1825
01:22:10,062 --> 01:22:11,062
No, Isha.

1826
01:22:12,687 --> 01:22:14,479
Only if he agreed.

1827
01:22:14,562 --> 01:22:16,062
I'd have given him
his fair share.

1828
01:22:16,062 --> 01:22:16,979
Fair share?

1829
01:22:17,062 --> 01:22:20,437
It's his company, okay?
He included you.

1830
01:22:20,562 --> 01:22:22,062
- And you!
- No...

1831
01:22:22,146 --> 01:22:24,312
Suman, I don't get
into their business...

1832
01:22:24,437 --> 01:22:26,354
Relations are like business
for you.

1833
01:22:26,646 --> 01:22:29,979
No one cares
for anyone in this room.

1834
01:22:30,437 --> 01:22:32,896
Everyone has a price.

1835
01:22:33,062 --> 01:22:34,854
Everything remains the same.
Okay?

1836
01:22:34,937 --> 01:22:37,604
Sandeep is still part of the company.
Nothing has changed.

1837
01:22:37,687 --> 01:22:39,354
We don't need your charity.

1838
01:22:39,437 --> 01:22:41,562
Nothing has changed?

1839
01:22:41,812 --> 01:22:43,396
Nothing has changed?

1840
01:22:43,562 --> 01:22:44,937
This party...

1841
01:22:45,187 --> 01:22:46,646
was there to make a deal?

1842
01:22:46,771 --> 01:22:47,979
- No.
- You're sick!

1843
01:22:48,062 --> 01:22:49,854
Yes, exactly!

1844
01:22:49,937 --> 01:22:52,062
- You guys are sick!
- Isha, no.

1845
01:22:52,312 --> 01:22:54,187
Yes, it was there
to make a deal.

1846
01:22:54,312 --> 01:22:57,521
When the cops were taking him away,
no one came to defend him.

1847
01:22:57,646 --> 01:22:59,562
Cat got your tongue.

1848
01:22:59,646 --> 01:23:01,687
It's only Sandeep...
How does it matter?

1849
01:23:01,771 --> 01:23:04,687
- Let him take the blame for murder.
- You'd never do this...

1850
01:23:04,812 --> 01:23:07,396
All my life I have lived
on your alms, but this!

1851
01:23:07,812 --> 01:23:10,771
Remember, pride comes
before the fall.

1852
01:23:10,812 --> 01:23:12,187
It will be the end of you!

1853
01:23:12,312 --> 01:23:15,312
- What lengths would you go to?
- Suman, please. We're leaving.

1854
01:23:15,437 --> 01:23:17,396
What are you capable of?
Did you kill him?

1855
01:23:17,437 --> 01:23:18,396
You killed him!

1856
01:23:18,562 --> 01:23:21,854
- You killed him!
- No, Isha. I didn't.

1857
01:23:21,937 --> 01:23:25,021
Did you?
Did he push you, Arun?

1858
01:23:25,062 --> 01:23:26,312
- Isha.
- You've done it.

1859
01:23:26,312 --> 01:23:27,271
Isha!

1860
01:23:27,396 --> 01:23:28,896
- Kumar, are you happy now?
- Did he push you?

1861
01:23:28,937 --> 01:23:30,646
- Are you happy?
- He is the one, right?

1862
01:23:30,771 --> 01:23:31,771
Isha!

1863
01:23:31,937 --> 01:23:32,937
Be quiet.

1864
01:23:34,937 --> 01:23:36,187
Inspector...

1865
01:23:37,812 --> 01:23:38,937
I killed him.

1866
01:23:39,062 --> 01:23:40,937
- Baba, stop it.
- Arrest me.

1867
01:23:42,062 --> 01:23:45,312
He gave us all a lot of grief.
He was like an open wound.

1868
01:23:46,687 --> 01:23:48,562
Don't be silly.
Just go to your room.

1869
01:23:48,687 --> 01:23:50,396
- You just go.
- Keep quiet.

1870
01:23:50,437 --> 01:23:52,062
You don't know a thing!

1871
01:23:52,312 --> 01:23:53,812
He was a monster!

1872
01:23:53,937 --> 01:23:55,896
- Arun.
- He hurt you too...

1873
01:23:56,021 --> 01:23:59,146
Did you not hear any door bang?

1874
01:23:59,187 --> 01:24:02,646
I should have done it
long time back.

1875
01:24:03,896 --> 01:24:05,562
He was forever a pain.

1876
01:24:07,062 --> 01:24:08,562
He was neither a good son.

1877
01:24:10,187 --> 01:24:11,771
Nor a good husband.

1878
01:24:13,312 --> 01:24:14,937
He couldn't even
be anyone's friend.

1879
01:24:19,937 --> 01:24:21,937
But I am his father.

1880
01:24:22,604 --> 01:24:24,854
I had to fulfill my duty
as his father.

1881
01:24:25,812 --> 01:24:30,437
- Inspector, let's end this.
- We'll do it.

1882
01:24:30,937 --> 01:24:33,646
Give us your statement first.
Tell me exactly how you did it.

1883
01:24:33,937 --> 01:24:36,687
Well...
Not much.

1884
01:24:37,146 --> 01:24:38,687
Everyone was asleep.

1885
01:24:39,854 --> 01:24:41,312
I came out here.

1886
01:24:41,521 --> 01:24:43,771
The knife was on the table.

1887
01:24:44,437 --> 01:24:46,937
I went behind him...
And put it to his neck...

1888
01:24:47,771 --> 01:24:49,187
Then I went back to my room.

1889
01:24:49,646 --> 01:24:53,312
The door banged shut.
I got startled.

1890
01:24:53,396 --> 01:24:54,812
What did you do
with the knife?

1891
01:24:54,937 --> 01:24:57,687
- Did you take it with you?
- Why would I take it with me?

1892
01:24:58,396 --> 01:25:01,312
- Left it here... On the table, probably.
- Sir...

1893
01:25:01,562 --> 01:25:02,896
Sir?

1894
01:25:03,812 --> 01:25:05,812
The knife was not on the table.

1895
01:25:07,437 --> 01:25:09,521
See, inspector.

1896
01:25:09,896 --> 01:25:11,271
I'm not lying.

1897
01:25:11,396 --> 01:25:12,771
You're not lying.

1898
01:25:15,021 --> 01:25:18,646
It's true that the sound of the door
came from your room.

1899
01:25:20,146 --> 01:25:23,521
Also true, that you're trying
to be a good father.

1900
01:25:25,562 --> 01:25:27,937
By trying to save your son.

1901
01:25:32,187 --> 01:25:33,812
Am I wrong, Arun?

1902
01:25:41,812 --> 01:25:44,812
Why did you have to speak?

1903
01:25:45,437 --> 01:25:48,187
It was getting to be fun.
Everybody's cover was getting blown!

1904
01:25:48,312 --> 01:25:49,396
What are you doing, Arun?

1905
01:25:49,562 --> 01:25:52,521
- What are you doing?
- You're the only sane one here, right?

1906
01:25:52,562 --> 01:25:53,896
- Arun!
- That's enough!

1907
01:25:54,021 --> 01:25:54,937
Arun is dead!

1908
01:25:56,146 --> 01:25:58,937
He was an open wound.
A stone around your neck?

1909
01:25:59,062 --> 01:26:00,187
Now you are free.

1910
01:26:00,312 --> 01:26:02,146
Now live happily ever after.

1911
01:26:03,812 --> 01:26:05,187
Is this statement enough?

1912
01:26:05,896 --> 01:26:07,687
So you admit
that you killed your brother?

1913
01:26:07,896 --> 01:26:09,146
You're a sub-inspector, right?

1914
01:26:09,312 --> 01:26:10,687
This will get you a promotion.

1915
01:26:11,437 --> 01:26:12,562
Yes, I did it.
Let's go.

1916
01:26:12,937 --> 01:26:13,937
Take him away.

1917
01:26:14,062 --> 01:26:15,146
Let's go.

1918
01:26:15,271 --> 01:26:16,187
Arun!

1919
01:26:16,354 --> 01:26:17,354
Arun!

1920
01:26:17,437 --> 01:26:19,396
- Arun!
- Why the hell did you do it, Arun?

1921
01:26:19,937 --> 01:26:21,271
You're asking me, Madh?

1922
01:26:21,437 --> 01:26:23,937
I did it because of you.
Because of all of you.

1923
01:26:24,062 --> 01:26:25,562
All of you
were always mean to him.

1924
01:26:26,187 --> 01:26:27,604
All of you are involved.

1925
01:26:30,187 --> 01:26:31,937
He cried himself to sleep
every night.

1926
01:26:33,062 --> 01:26:37,104
Every night!
Couldn't bear to see him like this.

1927
01:26:38,146 --> 01:26:39,771
Someone had to end it.
So, I did.

1928
01:26:40,062 --> 01:26:42,312
I have no regret.
I did the right thing.

1929
01:26:42,437 --> 01:26:43,771
Wa-wait a second.

1930
01:26:44,771 --> 01:26:45,896
Who did you kill?

1931
01:26:48,062 --> 01:26:50,521
You are the educated one, Doctor.
You tell me.

1932
01:26:51,146 --> 01:26:52,146
Was I wrong?

1933
01:26:52,687 --> 01:26:56,271
All of them used to avoid him
like the plague.

1934
01:26:56,937 --> 01:26:58,771
They tolerated him
because he's my brother.

1935
01:26:58,896 --> 01:27:02,396
Because they are all scared of me.

1936
01:27:05,937 --> 01:27:07,562
Not like he was living anyway.

1937
01:27:08,896 --> 01:27:10,562
He'd cut himself up three times.

1938
01:27:10,771 --> 01:27:12,562
So you just helped him along,
did you?

1939
01:27:12,687 --> 01:27:14,021
I delivered him!

1940
01:27:15,062 --> 01:27:16,521
I set him free.

1941
01:27:17,687 --> 01:27:19,229
Wherever he is,
he's happier now.

1942
01:27:19,271 --> 01:27:22,271
So all of you can buzz off
with your fricking fake grief.

1943
01:27:28,562 --> 01:27:30,396
Arun, my son.

1944
01:27:31,062 --> 01:27:32,271
Arun, my son.

1945
01:27:32,437 --> 01:27:34,437
Son... Son…

1946
01:27:35,146 --> 01:27:36,896
You more than anyone else,
old man...

1947
01:27:36,937 --> 01:27:39,396
You were the biggest pain
for both of us.

1948
01:27:40,187 --> 01:27:42,146
Please atone in peace, Daddy-o.

1949
01:27:42,812 --> 01:27:44,396
No one will trouble you anymore.

1950
01:27:46,187 --> 01:27:48,396
- Arun!
- He's not Arun.

1951
01:27:48,896 --> 01:27:50,521
What the hell just happened?

1952
01:27:51,021 --> 01:27:52,021
He switched.

1953
01:27:52,437 --> 01:27:54,187
- Switched?
- Who?

1954
01:27:54,437 --> 01:27:55,437
What?

1955
01:27:57,562 --> 01:27:59,812
He idolised Sohrab.
He wanted to be like him.

1956
01:28:00,937 --> 01:28:02,521
Sohrab was his hero.

1957
01:28:03,646 --> 01:28:05,187
Now he has become Sohrab.

1958
01:28:06,562 --> 01:28:08,562
That's not Arun you see there.

1959
01:28:09,312 --> 01:28:10,521
That's Sohrab.

1960
01:28:11,937 --> 01:28:13,937
Sandeep, give me a cigarette.

1961
01:28:18,937 --> 01:28:21,312
I think I might have to bear
some of the blame.

1962
01:28:24,187 --> 01:28:25,396
And you too, Madh.

1963
01:28:32,437 --> 01:28:33,646
If you could be
somebody else...

1964
01:28:33,771 --> 01:28:36,021
- We were free...
- Anybody else...

1965
01:28:36,146 --> 01:28:37,687
- ...free to choose.
- No...

1966
01:28:37,812 --> 01:28:39,229
We're all us, but you..

1967
01:28:39,312 --> 01:28:41,812
- Who would you be?
- I'll be Sohrab Handa!

1968
01:28:41,854 --> 01:28:43,187
Bro, I want to be you.

1969
01:28:43,187 --> 01:28:45,062
Are you saying we become
what we are given?

1970
01:28:45,271 --> 01:28:47,896
You're writing your own story.
You choose your hero.

1971
01:28:47,937 --> 01:28:48,812
Want some cake, tiger?

1972
01:28:48,896 --> 01:28:50,812
- ...and you become that.
- I'm me and you're you.

1973
01:28:50,937 --> 01:28:53,687
We make ourselves...

1974
01:28:53,812 --> 01:28:55,437
Want to cut it or stab it?

1975
01:28:55,562 --> 01:28:56,937
What did we choose?

1976
01:28:57,021 --> 01:28:58,646
Anybody else?
Who would you be?

1977
01:28:58,771 --> 01:29:00,146
What's in a name, Rose?

1978
01:29:00,271 --> 01:29:01,437
I'm me and you're you.

1979
01:29:01,687 --> 01:29:03,187
Survival... We lie to survive...

1980
01:29:04,021 --> 01:29:06,062
I can always aspire to be...

1981
01:29:06,187 --> 01:29:08,937
...nobler in the mind
to suffer the slings and arrows...

1982
01:29:09,187 --> 01:29:11,187
Why didn't you die
the moment you were born?

1983
01:29:11,437 --> 01:29:13,937
Or take arms
against a sea of troubles...

1984
01:29:15,104 --> 01:29:16,354
He became Sohrab.

1985
01:29:17,604 --> 01:29:18,562
But in the bargain

1986
01:29:18,604 --> 01:29:20,187
Sohrab became Arun in his head.

1987
01:29:21,187 --> 01:29:22,812
I suppose the only way...

1988
01:29:23,854 --> 01:29:25,396
to help him was...

1989
01:29:27,437 --> 01:29:29,937
He was right.
It was suicide in a way.

1990
01:29:34,937 --> 01:29:36,396
What is this rubbish?

1991
01:29:36,604 --> 01:29:39,187
- Who pushed him down?
- No one pushed him.

1992
01:29:40,104 --> 01:29:41,354
He jumped.

1993
01:29:44,479 --> 01:29:45,937
Bravo!

1994
01:29:46,021 --> 01:29:48,604
Everyone has gotten smarter
with the day break. Wow!

1995
01:31:06,729 --> 01:31:09,229
You had a good game going.
Well done.

1996
01:31:09,604 --> 01:31:11,146
So you do have some balls.

1997
01:31:12,437 --> 01:31:14,437
Be very careful
what you wish for.

1998
01:31:14,729 --> 01:31:16,187
Very careful.

1999
01:31:16,562 --> 01:31:17,562
Very careful.

2000
01:31:24,104 --> 01:31:25,104
Yes, sir.

2001
01:31:26,729 --> 01:31:27,729
Okay.

2002
01:31:30,354 --> 01:31:31,854
Let's take him to the station.

2003
01:32:39,187 --> 01:32:40,229
Both my sons...

2004
01:32:42,104 --> 01:32:44,187
I lost both of them at one go.

2005
01:33:22,687 --> 01:33:23,687
It's okay.

2006
01:33:24,104 --> 01:33:25,104
Take care.

2007
01:33:28,104 --> 01:33:29,312
Bye, Kumar.

2008
01:33:30,479 --> 01:33:31,854
Bye, Chandra.

2009
01:33:32,854 --> 01:33:34,104
Bye, Maddy.

2010
01:33:34,354 --> 01:33:35,562
Bye, Doctor.

2011
01:33:38,854 --> 01:33:39,771
Nena?

2012
01:33:40,104 --> 01:33:42,104
Carry on, Kumar.
I'll see you at the studio.

2013
01:33:42,312 --> 01:33:43,562
I'm coming with Suman.

2014
01:33:44,479 --> 01:33:46,729
Why are you going
with Suman?

2015
01:33:47,187 --> 01:33:48,062
Nena.

2016
01:33:48,187 --> 01:33:49,854
- Satya!
- Yes, ma'am.

2017
01:33:52,562 --> 01:33:54,729
Sometimes, these games
don't turn out so well.

2018
01:33:55,104 --> 01:33:57,229
It's not your fault.
Please don't blame yourself.

2019
01:33:57,354 --> 01:33:58,729
I should have seen it earlier...

2020
01:33:59,354 --> 01:34:00,604
It's not you.

2021
01:34:01,354 --> 01:34:02,354
It's us.

2022
01:34:03,187 --> 01:34:04,937
We choose to fall
every single time.

2023
01:34:06,354 --> 01:34:07,354
We're doomed.

2024
01:34:08,187 --> 01:34:09,687
I hope you're wrong.

2025
01:34:10,812 --> 01:34:11,812
Good luck, Professor.

2026
01:34:14,187 --> 01:34:16,854
Nena, come with me, please.

2027
01:34:17,187 --> 01:34:18,604
Just carry on.
I'll see you there.

2028
01:34:23,479 --> 01:34:24,479
Professor.

2029
01:34:27,479 --> 01:34:29,187
What will save us, Professor?

2030
01:34:32,479 --> 01:34:33,604
Beauty.

2031
01:35:16,187 --> 01:35:17,312
Did you have the cake?

2032
01:35:18,187 --> 01:35:19,187
No?

2033
01:35:20,104 --> 01:35:21,354
Didn't even taste it?

2034
01:35:21,479 --> 01:35:22,729
It was a good cake!

2035
01:35:22,937 --> 01:35:23,937
Very expensive.

2036
01:35:28,062 --> 01:35:29,604
What's your salary?

2037
01:35:30,979 --> 01:35:32,187
Fifteen thousand?

2038
01:35:32,812 --> 01:35:34,229
Twenty grand with bribes.

2039
01:35:34,604 --> 01:35:36,062
- Amar ji.
- Yes, sir.

2040
01:35:36,312 --> 01:35:38,437
Don't talk to him.
He's crazy.

2041
01:35:39,937 --> 01:35:42,479
It's okay,
If dry bread is your fate

2042
01:35:42,729 --> 01:35:44,229
how will you ever eat cake?

2043
01:35:46,062 --> 01:35:47,729
Talk to me.

2044
01:35:48,187 --> 01:35:49,479
Or I'll get bored.

2045
01:36:00,104 --> 01:36:01,437
Hey, look there.
See that?

2046
01:36:03,104 --> 01:36:06,729
What an amazing job He has done!

2047
01:36:08,312 --> 01:36:10,979
He just messed up
while making humans.

2048
01:36:37,854 --> 01:36:42,562
"A wayward weird worrying thing"

2049
01:36:44,687 --> 01:36:49,229
"Has sunk within me"

2050
01:36:51,812 --> 01:36:56,937
"Some wordless, worthless thing"

2051
01:36:58,812 --> 01:37:03,812
"Is stuck within me"

2052
01:37:34,354 --> 01:37:39,312
"He drowned, sometimes he swam"

2053
01:37:41,437 --> 01:37:45,979
"He clung to me, sometimes he died"

2054
01:37:48,187 --> 01:37:53,229
"The life of the party,
Or a maudlin thing"

2055
01:37:55,479 --> 01:37:58,354
"Kicked the door open with a sickness"

2056
01:37:58,604 --> 01:38:01,354
"And no cure for him"

2057
01:38:02,229 --> 01:38:04,604
"Who is he, who is he?"

2058
01:38:05,437 --> 01:38:07,979
"Who could he be?"

2059
01:38:08,979 --> 01:38:13,729
"Who is he,
who could he be?"

2060
01:38:44,604 --> 01:38:47,437
"Friends with their hands"

2061
01:38:47,479 --> 01:38:50,854
"Full of deceits"

2062
01:38:52,104 --> 01:38:56,687
"Even the good ones"

2063
01:38:57,937 --> 01:39:00,479
"Muddy with guilt"

2064
01:39:01,104 --> 01:39:04,479
"The lies were inexhaustible"

2065
01:39:04,854 --> 01:39:08,521
"The masks fixed
Tightly to their skin"

2066
01:39:09,687 --> 01:39:12,479
"Clawed and clawed and clawed"

2067
01:39:12,979 --> 01:39:16,104
"How I clawed at their facades"

2068
01:39:16,312 --> 01:39:17,979
"How I ripped into their faces"

2069
01:39:18,187 --> 01:39:19,729
"How I strangled each one's neck

2070
01:39:20,104 --> 01:39:23,062
"Until the truth came out,
Sputtering, bleeding"

2071
01:39:23,312 --> 01:39:26,354
"From the shadows for so long"

2072
01:39:26,854 --> 01:39:29,854
"A wayward weird worrying thing"

2073
01:39:29,979 --> 01:39:31,479
"Is stuck within me"

2074
01:39:33,979 --> 01:39:36,979
"Some wordless, worthless thing"

2075
01:39:37,229 --> 01:39:40,479
"Has sunk within me"
